title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake chocolate cake according to instructions on box.
Prepare chocolate pudding.
Crush the Skor bars.
Layer in a medium bowl in the following order:
cake, pudding, Cool Whip and Skor bars. Repeat.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand 20 minutes or until cool.

title: sauerbraten hamburger patties
directions: Crumble bread well; mix with meat in a fairly large bowl.
Add onion, egg and salt; mix thoroughly.
Shape mixture into small patties, approximately 1/2-inch thick by 2 inches diameter.
Brown well on both sides, in either oil or margarine, in a large skillet.
Brown 2 or 3 batches.
Drain well on paper towels; set aside.

title: cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Add butter and cheese.
Mix well.
Add flour slowly.
Mix well, then carefully add Rice Krispies so as not to crush them. Bake until they are a golden brown.
Makes 150.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place sugar and milk in heavy 3 quart sauce pan.
Heat over medium heat for 3 minutes; remove form heat.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth; add marshmallow cream and continue to stir until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Let cool until firm.

title: best cherry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; let stand for 15 minutes.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Add top pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.

title: homemade crackers
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder into a bowl.
Cut in the butter until very fine.
Add milk and egg to make a stiff dough and knead thoroughly, about 5 minutes.
On a lightly floured surface, roll out dough until very thin and cut into squares or rounds (whatever shape and size you like) and place on a lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Prick with a fork and bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly brown.
You will need to keep an eye on them until you determine the time in your particular oven.

title: kitchen sink tomato sandwich
directions: In the peak of the tomato season, chill 1 very large or 2 medium tomatoes that have been vine-ripened and have a good acidy-bite to their taste.
Take 2 slices of bread, slice the tomato 1/4-inch thick.
Salt and pepper that layer.
Add another layer of sliced tomato and again salt and pepper.
Place the other piece of bread on top of this, roll up your sleeves, and commence to eat over the kitchen sink while the juice runs down your elbows.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients in blender.
Hollow out center of bread.
Tear bread from center into bite-sized pieces and place around outside of loaf.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, oil, confectioners sugar and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, flour, vanilla, soda, salt and cream of tartar. Roll in balls and press in pan with sugar covered glass.
Bake at 350°.

title: buttermilk apple cake
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients; add eggs and beat well. Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in apples.
Pour into oblong pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar, nuts and cinnamon over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix sugar and butter well.
Add eggs, mixing well after each. Add flour; stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a greased and floured oblong pan.
Cut when cool.

title: wendy's lemon parmesan chicken
directions: When I prepare this recipe, I usually use an entire bag of boneless skinless chicken from Sam's, so therefore, I really don't measure anything.

title: two egg chess pie
directions: Stir well.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake for 45 minutes in 325° oven until done.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with crackers or as sandwiches.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, celery and salt in saucepan. Add just enough water to cover. Cook 10-15 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Do not drain. Mash vegetables slightly. Stir in milk, butter, parsley and pepper. Heat, but do not allow to boil. Just before serving, add cheese; stir to melt.

title: chicken wellington squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons of margarine until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Separate crescent dough.
Press dough to form 4 x 6-inch rectangles.
Spoon 1/3 to 1/2 cup meat mixture into center of rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to top center of chicken mixture.
Twist slightly and pinch edges to seal.
Brush with or dip in reserved melted margarine.
Dip in crushed croutons.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mash avocados and mix well with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix together.

title: green goddess dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, in order given, and serve on lettuce.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix pumpkin, eggs and milk; pour over first layer.
Mix 1 cup cake mix, 1/4 cup margarine, cinnamon and sugar with fork and sprinkle over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
When cool, top with Cool Whip.

title: rice croquettes(italian style "arancini")
directions: In a saucepan, heat butter and saute onion until golden.
Add rice; saute over medium heat, stirring constantly, about 2 minutes.
Do not let rice brown.
Add 1/2 cup chicken broth.
When liquid is absorbed, which is almost immediately, add an additional cup of broth.
Lower heat; simmer slowly until the broth is almost absorbed again, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining chicken broth; simmer until rice has absorbed all the liquid.
Stir the grated cheese into the rice; set aside until cooled slightly.
Taste for salt and add, if needed.
Stir in eggs, then refrigerate rice mixture until cold or until ready to use.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Beat egg.
Add flour and slowly add milk.
Beat with a wire whisk to prevent lumps.
Coat the onions and drop a ring at a time in hot grease.
Brown on one side, then turn over.
Remove to paper towel to drain.
Dropping batter directly into grease gives you "crunchies."

title: taffy chips
directions: Boil molasses, sugar, vinegar and butter slowly until mixture hardens when tested in cold water.
Stir gently as syrup thickens. Add vanilla.
Pour on a buttered plate and cool.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
When cool, melt chocolate over warm water and dip the pieces in it.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: mock-yaksoba
directions: In a large saucepan, boil the Ramen noodles (without the sauce packs).
Drain in strainer while rinsing thoroughly with cool water (until noodles aren't sticky).
Set aside.

title: nut cake
directions: Beat the butter and sugar to a cream; add the well beaten yolks of the eggs, then the milk, chopped nuts and extract.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt and add to the other ingredients.
Bake in a loaf cake pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients and set aside. Mix oil, sugar and eggs. Add dry ingredients, beating after each addition. Mix well and add carrots and nuts. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, cornstarch, butter and lemon rind in a small saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is bubbly and thick.
Cool to room temperature.
Put pie crust on bottom and top.
Bake in a 350° oven until crust is golden brown.

title: super omelet
directions: Brown sausage in frying pan and drain grease.
Fluff eggs with whip.
Mix browned sausage, cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam, layer bottom with 5 of the biscuits, mashing biscuits out.
Pour mixture over biscuits.
Mash other 5 biscuits and place on top.
Cook at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Omelet is done when biscuits are brown.

title: white grape wedding punch(caffeine-free)
directions: Mix as needed at time of party.
Use 2 cans of water for each can of grape juice (not 3).
Use 3 cans of water for each can of frozen lemonade.
Chill all ingredients in advance.
To make an ice ring, to float, use lemonade, and decorate with lime slices.

title: mexican salad
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
Drain fat.
Break up lettuce and cube tomatoes.
Add cheese, crumbled Doritos and Tabasco sauce to taste. Add hamburger and toss.
Add dressing and toss.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook that mixture until it is clear.
Let it cool, then add 1 1/2 cups mayonnaise and 1/4 cup mustard to it.
Take that mixture and pour over macaroni mixture and mix well.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; press into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread rolls into 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Combine next 4 ingredients and spread on cooled crust.
Top with finely chopped vegetables.

title: lamb in dill sauce
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil and saute onion in a frying pan. Remove with a slotted spoon to a mixing bowl and let cool.
Add meat, crumbs, seasoning, beaten egg, 2 teaspoons dill, parsley and Worcestershire.
Mix well and form into meatballs.
Add remaining oil to frying pan and saute meatballs about 8 minutes, shaking pan to keep from sticking.
Remove to a platter and keep warm.
Mix egg yolks, lemon juice and a small amount of sour cream in a small bowl.
Add to the pan juices, blending well.
Then add remaining sour cream and dill.
Serve meatballs over noodles, ladling the sauce over all.
Serves 4.

title: chop bread pepperoni-cheese
directions: Thaw dough.
Pat into a 10-inch circle, cover and let rise about 1 hour, until doubled.
Spread pizza sauce over dough. Sprinkle with oregano, pepperoni and cheese.
Draw dough up around filling.
With a large knife slice bundle 5 or 6 times across, then 5 or 6 times the other direction.
With knife, gently mix by lifting dough and pizza mixture from bottom and piling it on top. Pieces should be 2-inch squares.
Mound on greased sheet, reshaping in a circle.
Make sure most of the filling touches the dough. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Peel and core apples; do not cut in half.
Combine and heat sugar, water, vinegar, red coloring, red hots and cinnamon until red hots are dissolved.
Add peeled and cored whole apples to this syrup.
Cook in pan on top of stove until tender (not mushy). Turn while cooking so red hot candy syrup can soak into all of apples.
When done, place in large flat pan.
Pour leftover syrup over cooked apples.
Chill overnight.

title: chewy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with wax paper.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Dice garlic leaves and mushroom stems.
In large frying pan, put 3/4 can tomato sauce and 3/4 can water.
Saute diced garlic and mushroom stems, adding a little pepper.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms.
Pour over bread cubes in a very large bowl.
Add all seasonings and toss together well.
Pour in enough broth to moisten.
Add beaten eggs and mix together well.
Pack lightly into crock-pot. Cover and set on high for 45 minutes.
Reduce to low and cook for 4 to 8 hours.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix corn muffin mix with egg and milk.
Use bacon grease to grease muffin pans.
Blend in peppers, cheese, bacon and onions. Fill muffin cups about half full.
Bake 15-20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 12 muffins.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and sugar, then add to mixture once it is lukewarm.
Add 12 to 14 cups white flour or enough to make soft dough.
You can mix this in evening and cover.
Put in cool place overnight.
Cut in morning.
Use plenty of flour to work with.
Let rise; fry. Yields 6 to 7 dozen.

title: oven cooked chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and lay in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix 2 teaspoons A.1. steak sauce, 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce and a dash of seasoning salt in 2 cans of cream of chicken soup.
Pour over chicken.
Cover in foil. Bake about 2 hours at 300°.
Uncover and let brown.

title: aunt margaret's hamburg dish
directions: Cook macaroni;	add
a little butter in the pot.
Brown beef and
onion;
sprinkle
with salt, pepper and garlic salt. Add 1 1/3 cups cheese.
Heat and add tomato sauce and macaroni.
Pour into
a
greased 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle with the rest of the cheese.

title: quiche loraine
directions: Bake pie crust 3 minutes at 400°.
Prick with fork and bake 5 more minutes. Saute onion in butter. Combine all ingredients and pour into crust.
If not enough to fill, beat one more egg with 1/2 cup cream.
Bake 1 hour or until set.
Let set before cutting.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Stir well.
Pour into muffin pan.
Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon brown sugar on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 22 minutes.
Makes 10. Freezes well.

title: festive party mix
directions: Microwave margarine in deep 3-quart glass casserole on High for 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and garlic powder.
Add cereals, peanuts and crackers; stir to coat.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 6 to 7 minutes or until cereal is crisp.
Spread on paper towels to cool. Store in airtight container.

title: strawberry banana jello salad
directions: Combine 1 cup boiling water with one package of Jell-O.
Mix in one frozen package of strawberries and 2 bananas, cut in slices. Set in refrigerator to set.
Spread with sour cream and sprinkle nuts on top of this.
Fix second Jell-O the same way and place on top with strawberries and bananas.

title: beef goulash
directions: Cut meat into thin strips 1/4 inch thick and 2 inches long. Sprinkle with black pepper and paprika.
Heat the oil in a large skillet and brown the meat 3 minutes.
Transfer meat to another skillet.

title: potato delight
directions: Boil potatoes as for potato salad.
Add potatoes and onions according to how much you want to make.
Mix cheese and olives and pour melted oleo over the top (for a medium casserole melt 1/2 stick).
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and is bubbly.

title: judy's lemon-pepper chicken
directions: Roll chicken breast in butter.
Put lemon pepper spice on chicken breast.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: krunchy bars
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and cream to soft ball stage.
Add vanilla after soft ball stage.
Pour boiled mixture over the cereal and peanuts and mix well.
Put in buttered cookie sheet and press firmly.
Cut into bars.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add flours.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Press into a greased 12 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until brown (20 to 30 minutes).
Cool for 10 minutes.
Cut into fingers.
Dredge with sugar.
Store in airtight container.

title: butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake until set in a moderate oven.

title: chocolate pie(makes two pies)
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Mix cocoa with sugar.
Add to eggs.
Add condensed milk, vanilla and melted butter.
Bake in two unbaked pie shells, placed on a cookie sheet for 30 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Do not overbake!

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in 6 cups of water.
Drain and rinse well. Put beans and bone(s) in 3 quarts of water. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: ham and cheese pie
directions: Separate rolls.
Pull dough into 8 triangles.
Place 5 triangles in a 9-inch pie pan, pressing together to form crust.

title: dill weed bread dip
directions: Make the night before.
Hollow out loaf of round rye bread in small pieces.
Put dip in hole of bread and use small pieces of bread for dipping.

title: lucky cajun peas for new years day
directions: In large 6-quart pot, cook bacon till cooked through. Add onion, green pepper, celery and garlic and cook 7-10 minutes or until vegetables are soft. Stir in black-eyed peas, thyme, black pepper, cayenne and chicken stock. Reduce heat to medium-low. Cook, covered, until peas are tender enough to fall apart and liquid is soupy, about 1 1/2 hours. Stir often to prevent sticking.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except dressing and Fritos before you are ready to eat.
When you are ready to serve the salad, mix in Fritos and dressing.

title: snappy baked fruit
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine peaches, pears and lemon peel; mix well.
Divide fruit mixture evenly among six (6-ounce) custard cups.
In small bowl, combine crushed cookies and margarine.
Mix well.
Sprinkle evenly over fruit.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand 24 hours before serving.

title: easy breakfast rolls
directions: Spread syrup on half pieces of buns.
Sprinkle with pecans. Heat in oven at 350° until hot.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple with pudding mix.
Add pecans and marshmallows. Mix in Cool Whip, reserving some for topping.
Mix all ingredients and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: sour cream noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water according to package directions.
Rinse and drain.
In skillet, brown the meat in butter.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt, then the tomato sauce. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine the cottage cheese, sour cream and chopped onions with the noodles.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Top with the meat mixture.
Sprinkle the shredded cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This dish can be frozen.
It is best made the day before.
This is really good.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter into eggs; add cheese.
Add salt, muffin mix, broccoli and onion.
Pour into a greased pan (cast-iron 10-inch skillet works best) and bake at 400° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: carrot bars
directions: Mix together well.
Grease and flour pan, 2 x 9 x 13-inch. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in bars.

title: creamy beans
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine beans, soup and cheese in a casserole dish.
Stir well.
Sprinkle French fried onions over beans.
Bake for 25 minutes or until beans are bubbly in the center.

title: orange drop donuts
directions: Mix in order given, then drop by spoonfuls into hot grease and fry slowly.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine until tender.
Mix remaining ingredients with onions.
Bake in 450° oven until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: In casserole, alternate layers, beginning with crumbs and then sauce until all is completed.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Crush garlic in 1 teaspoon salt.
Saute mushrooms in olive oil.
Combine with remaining ingredients in stainless or glass bowl.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours or overnight.
Serve with garlic croutons, if desired.

title: grandma's pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine with extract.
Add sugar gradually, creaming well.
Add beaten eggs in thirds, beating well after each addition.
Thoroughly blend in chopped pecans, along with salt and syrup.
Turn into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350°.
Arrange pecan halves on top.
Continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Shake all together until well blended.
Store in airtight container.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Peel and cook squash in water, until done.
Mash; add salt and pepper to taste.
Add margarine to hot squash.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: big mama's corn and cheese casserole
directions: *Fresh corn is best.

title: rice
directions: Place rice in a baking dish.
Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over rice; stir.
Cover with tight fitting lid or foil and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot spicy punch
directions: Dissolve liquids and sugar.
Place in percolator.
Put filter in percolator basket and place spices in basket.
Perk!!

title: pizzaritos
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add 1/2 can pizza sauce, spices and toppings.
Simmer 5 minutes until toppings such as onions are tender.
Spoon 2 to 3 tablespoons of mixture into center of tortilla shell.
Sprinkle cheese onto meat.
Fold as a burrito, or just roll.
Arrange in microwavable dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and drizzle with remaining sauce.
Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 way through time.

title: peach alaska
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Blend in whipped topping and peaches.
Place mixture in a glass dish; chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Line pan with foil.
Put in chicken breasts; pour sauce over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: cheesy hash brown casserole
directions: Mix altogether.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and cut up the vegetables.

title: ranchero tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef in oil.
Add chopped onion and cook until wilted.
Add tomatoes and liquid from corn.
Stir in corn meal.
Simmer about 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add salt, chili powder, drained corn and ripe olives.
Turn into a 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grandmother's old-fashioned cinnamon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter and shortening until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Make brine from all ingredients (except meat) and leave overnight at room temperature.
Stir once or twice.
Pour over meat.
Bake in 300° oven, 2 hours.
Serve with Kloese (dumplings) or cooked noodles.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions; let cool. Prick holes in the top of brownies with a fork and pour coffee or coffee liqueur over brownies; set aside.
Prepare chocolate mousse according to package directions.
Break up the toffee bars in food processor or tap lightly with a hammer.
Break up half the brownies into small pieces and place in the bottom of a large glass bowl or trifle dish.
Cover with half the mousse, then half the candy and half the Cool Whip.
Repeat layers with the remaining ingredients; chill and serve.

title: best cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water for 3 minutes.
Add cake mix, 1 cup flour, eggs, oil and salt.
Beat until bubbly.
Add balance of flour to make soft dough.
Knead lightly.
Let rise until double. Roll out about 1/4-inch thick (it's easier if dough is divided in half).
Spread with margarine, sugar and cinnamon.
Raisins may be added, too.
Roll as jelly roll and cut.
Raise until double. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Ice while warm.
Makes about 24 that stay soft and are wonderful served warm.

title: chocolate supreme pie
directions: Cook pecans in bottom of pie crust.
Slice a layer of bananas over cooled crust.
Add cooked and cooled filling; garnish with whip cream.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and softened margarine and press into bottom of 9 x 11 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Use wok or heavy skillet and medium heat.
Making sure it is hot, add 3 tablespoons margarine and the olive oil.
When butter is melted, add onion, garlic, lemon juice and salt.
Cook until onion is limp.
Should take about 30 seconds.
Turn heat on high. Add shrimp; stir-fry until shrimp turn pink, approximately 2 to 3 minutes.
Add lemon peel, parsley and hot pepper seasoning to taste.
Garnish with lemon wedge; squeeze on each serving.
Serve with buttered rice.

title: smith college fudge
directions: Stir together in a large saucepan the sugar, brown sugar, corn syrup, milk and butter.
Bring to boil on high heat, then turn heat to medium.
Add 2 squares chocolate.
When candy is ready (hardens in cold water), remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into flat, shallow pan.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: sly devil eggs
directions: Butter a 9-inch casserole dish.
Cut eggs in half, remove yolks.
Mix yolks with melted butter, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, ham and scallions.
Blend until smooth, stuff the mixture into egg halves.
Arrange egg halves in the buttered dish.
Melt remaining butter in saucepan, stirring flour to form a paste, and cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Blend in milk and season with salt and pepper.
Heat until thickened, pour sauce over eggs and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° in oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over toasted English muffins.

title: strawberry dumplings
directions: Combine strawberries, sugar and water into medium cooker. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Mix flour, shortening and milk into bowl.
When strawberries are cooked, drop flour mixture by the spoonfuls into strawberries.
Cook on low heat until dumplings are done.
Serve with Cool Whip on top in a bowl.
Any fruit, frozen, can be cooked and served the same way.

title: gram boyd's stir-n-roll pie crust
directions: Easy!
Put everything in a bowl together; stir and roll.

title: apricot nut salad
directions: Bring to a boil sugar, water, baby food, jello and pineapple. Remove from heat and add cream cheese.
Let cool.
Whip well chilled evaporated milk until stiff.
Fold cooled mixture into milk.
Sprinkle with nuts and chill.

title: yellow cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add eggs one at a time, then dry ingredients with milk, then vanilla.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or two layer cake pans.
Bake in a 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes a nice cake for birthday or any other occasion.

title: fudge brownies
directions: In bowl, combine sugars, flour, egg substitute, margarine and cocoa until well blended.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Spread in well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Wrap and store at room temperature for up to 4 days.
Dust with confectioners sugar before serving.
Makes 36; 85 calories; 30 mg. sodium; 3 grams fat per brownie.

title: apple bread
directions: Peel and dice 2 cups apples.
Add 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Let stand 1 hour.
Add 1 egg, 1 1/2 cup flour, 1/2 cup cooking oil, 1 teaspoon soda, 1/4 teaspoons salt and 1 cup pecans chopped.
Put in greased loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: frozen punch
directions: Mix together and sugar to taste. Freeze. Thaw mix with hand mixer. Add 1 large ginger ale.

title: dutch's apple pie
directions: Arrange apples in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of sugar. Mix together second half of sugar, spices, flour and milk. Pour over apples.
Cook at 275° until brown.

title: date nut bars
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco until coarse.
Stir in vanilla, milk and egg.
Add nuts and dates.
mixture will be rather stiff.
Place in a greased 2 x 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo syrup and water in heavy saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add peanuts and cook until honey colored and peanuts pop. Add baking soda and mix well.
Pour onto buttered pan and let cool.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine the syrup, sugar, butter and salt together and cook over medium heat until the sugar dissolves. Add the peanuts. Stir constantly until peanuts become light brown.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in the soda.
Spread thinly on greased shallow pan.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all thoroughly by hand; pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Use ground beef to make 1 recipe of your favorite meat loaf. Place meat loaf mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer drained green beans, mushroom soup and Tater Tots; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Place hen or 2 fryers in large boiler.
Cover with water and salt to taste.
Cook until tender.
Crumble loaf bread and corn bread in large mixing bowl.
Add celery, onion, sage, poultry seasoning, black pepper and margarine.
Have chicken broth boiling. Pour this over mixture.
Mash with potato masher until well blended and very moist.
Add raw eggs and mix well.
Pour into pan, approximately 18 x 12-inch that has been well-greased.
Bake at 400° until done or about 30 minutes.
Serves around 20.

title: tomato salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes; I take the skins off and some seeds out.
Chop jalapeno peppers (wear gloves!).
Chop onion.
Do not cook. Simply mix all ingredients well.
Can add more hot peppers if you like.
Store in refrigerator, covered.

title: joanne's frontier soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large kettle.
Bring to boil.
Stir frequently.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: chicken milano
directions: In a 10 inch skillet, cook onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add chicken and cook until no longer pink.
Stir in tomato soup and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Serve over rice.
Serves:

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water on 2 cups of 100% Bran and let cool.
Blend sugar, oleo and eggs.
Add bran mixture to creamed oleo, sugar and eggs.
Mix flour, soda, salt and all-bran.
Add 1 quart buttermilk and the flour mixture.
Mix all together.
You can add dates, raisins or nuts when ready to bake.
Put batter in tight plastic container (I use 1 gallon ice cream bucket) and you can keep it in refrigerator up to six weeks.
Store overnight before using.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs or potato chips.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: First we just get them out of the box.
And then we take them and put them right in the pot.
Then we put sprinkle cheese on them and then Eli likes sauce on them but I only like sprinkle cheese on them.
And then we eat them!

title: chili-mac in a hurry
directions: Cover macaroni in a large bowl with boiling water.

Let stand. Brown the beef and onion in skillet. Add chili powder. Drain macaroni. Rinse in cold water. Add macaroni and remaining items to skillet. Mix thoroughly and bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle servings with cheese, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and egg yolks.
Add syrup, vanilla and pecans.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into unbaked deep dish pie shell or 2 regular size pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bleu cheese party spread
directions: Soften gelatin and water in a small pan.
Bring to just a boil, stirring to dissolve gelatin, and remove from heat.
Set aside. Combine sour cream, cheeses and spices in a processor container or mixer bowl and blend well.
Add gelatin and blend again.
Pour into a 10-inch decorative pie plate and refrigerate until firm, overnight is best.
Garnish with shrimp, onion, olives, cheese and tomatoes as desired.
Serve with crackers or bread rounds.

title: chicken parisienne(crock-pot recipe or dutch oven)
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts lightly with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place chicken breasts in crock-pot (Dutch oven).

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in condensed milk, lime juice, rind and food coloring (optional).
In small bowl, stiffly beat 1 egg white; fold into milk mixture.
Turn into shell.
Beat reserved egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff.
Spread meringue on pie, sealing carefully edge of shell.
Bake 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.
Cool.
Chill before serving.

title: barbecue burgers
directions: Combine above ingredients. Form patties. Spray pan with Pam and place patties in pan.
Put a slice of onion on each patty. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: grilled pork tenderloins
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a shallow dish.
Add pork and turn to coat.
(Can use Ziploc bag.)
Cover and refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Cook tenderloins, covered with grill lid, over medium coals (350° to 400°) for 20 minutes or until a meat thermometer inserted in thickest portion registers 160°, turning once.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: scripture cake(king james version)
directions: Cream Judges 5:25.
Add Jeremiah 6:20 and Samuel 14:25.
Add Jeremiah 17:11 and do as in Proverbs 23:14 after each.
Sift together 1 Kings 4:22 and Leviticus 2:13, Amos 4:5 and 1 Kings 10:2.
Do Proverbs 23:14 until well mixed.
Add dry ingredients and Hebrews 5:13 alternately to creamed mixture.
What the Kingdom of Heaven is like unto, follow Solomon's advice in Proverbs 23:14 and when this has been done, add 1 Samuel 30:12 and Numbers 17:8. Continue Proverbs 23:14 until thoroughly blended.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Loosen with spatula and cool on rack.

title: low-fat microwave lasagna
directions: Brown turkey and Italian sausage; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water and heat through.
Meanwhile, combine cottage cheese, egg, salt and pepper.
Spoon 1/2 cup sauce into 12 x 8-inch baking dish (microwave-safe).
Alternately layer noodles, egg mixture, Mozzarella cheese and sauce, forming 3 layers.
Cook, covered, with plastic wrap, on High for 8 minutes and on Medium-low for 35 to 38 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Let stand, covered, for 15 minutes before serving.

title: scallop fettuccine
directions: *May also use crabmeat.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil water and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add tea bags and spices. Allow mixture to stand until it reaches room temperature. Add lemon juice and orange frozen concentrate.
Strain. Serve iced or hot.

title: overnight green pea salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients.
Seal with mayonnaise and sprinkle with sugar.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight. Layer tomatoes (sliced and cut), eggs and bacon.
Cover with cheese.

title: jean's apple pie
directions: Mix apples and water in casserole dish.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top.
Cut each slice of bread into four strips. Cover apples with strips.
Melt margarine; add sugar, water, egg, flour and vanilla.
Mix well and pour over bread strips.
Cover good.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chilled fruit salad
directions: Mix vanilla pudding and tang together. Add all fruit into a bowl and pour pudding mixture
over fruit and stir. Chill.

title: apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray muffin tin with Pam.
Mix dry ingredients well.
Mix wet ingredients well.
Mix all together only until dry ingredients are slightly moist and lumpy.
Fill tins about 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes until light brown.
These will freeze well.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes,
soups
and
dip	in
bowl.
Add salt and pepper.
Place
in	3
1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1
hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top as soon as removed from
oven.
Cover	with foil until cheese has melted. Good for potluck dinners.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add the eggs, 1 at a time.
Add pumpkin. Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon; add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Add pecans.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Mix together well and chill.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and bake at 325 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable medley
directions: *Example: Broccoli, carrots, cauliflower, green beans.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients, except chips or cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with either chips or cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce(family recipe)
directions: Heat and try to keep warm while using.
You can also add 1 can tomato sauce.
Good on any meats on the grill.

title: taco pie
directions: Bake pie crust until golden, according to package directions. In a skillet, brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in olives, tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Spoon meat mixture into pie shell.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn and milk in a medium bowl.
Mix egg whites, sugar and flour in a small bowl and beat lightly with a fork.
Add egg whites to corn mixture and mix well.
Pour into a small sprayed (nonfat spray) casserole dish or pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes (depending on thickness).
Yields 4 servings.
Has 170 calories, fat free.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Beat eggs; add margarine and sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes and cool.
Mix graham cracker crumbs, coconut, nut meats and marshmallows.
Mix into mixture; pat in 9 x 13-inch pan and press down.
Top with butterscotch chips, melted and peanut butter; spread on top.
Cut into bars.

title: praline pecan crunch
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal and pecans in a 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside.

title: coconut pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into buttered pie plates.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hamburger cheese dip
directions: Cook ground meat with onion until done.
On low heat, after draining meat, add remaining ingredients.
Cook until all cheese is melted.
Makes a great dip.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Saute mushrooms in 5 tablespoons margarine 5 minutes. Add flour and salt until frothy, stirring constantly.
Add onion juice. Stir. Add cream gradually, stirring constantly.
Add chicken, paprika and pepper. Cook over low heat until thickened.

title: chile
directions: Brown ground beef in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add onion, tomatoes, chile beans, tomato sauce, chili powder and chile mix.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pepper steak with rice
directions: Slice steak into 1/4-inch strips.
Brown steak in oil.
Add cornstarch.
Stir until cornstarch is mixed well with steak.
Add broth, water chestnuts, soy sauce and bell peppers.
Simmer for approximately 10 minutes.
Add rice.
Cover and let set until rice is fluffy approximately 10 minutes.

title: chicken corn soup with rivels
directions: About
5 hours before serving:	In large kettle combine chicken
with
chopped
onion, 1 tablespoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper
and
enough
water to cover the chicken.
Simmer, covered, about
hours or until chicken is almost tender. Remove chicken from broth, discard skin and bones and then cut into bite-size pieces.
Return
to
broth
with chopped celery and corn.
Continue simmering, covered, about 20 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside. Work shortening in bowl until creamy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with mashed bananas, a small amount at a time, beating after each addition until smooth.
Fold in chopped nuts. Turn into a well greased loaf pan, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inches.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool slightly; turn out of pan.
Enjoy!

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: In a saucepan, bring 1 cup water to boil; add cauliflower. Cook as directed.
Remove from water; set aside 1 cup cauliflower for garnish.
Whip celery soup in saucepan adding milk.
Add cauliflower and cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring until boiling.
Place 2 cups of soup into a blender.
Puree; do the rest of the soup.
Heat soup again, adding the remaining cauliflower. Garnish with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: pepsi chicken
directions: Melt oleo in electric skillet. Add remainder of ingredients and cook at 200° for 2 hours.

title: anytime bran muffins
directions: In large bowl mix bran cereal, flour, sugar, nuts, soda and salt.
Make a well in center.
In another bowl beat together eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened (will be thick). Cover and store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.
Use as needed.

title: dewberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients together except berries.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into dish over margarine.
Place fruit evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Combine and chill.
Serve in punch bowl over an ice ring.

title: crumb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl combine crumbs, coconut, nuts, baking powder and salt.
In a larger bowl beat egg whites until they stand in peaks.
Fold in sugar with a wooden spoon, then fold in crumb mix. Spoon into a greased pie pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Serve with whipped topping and garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns for 30 minutes.
Melt 1 1/2 sticks butter. Mix butter with all ingredients except 1/2 cup corn flakes in a casserole dish.
Use 1/2 stick melted butter and corn flakes for topping.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: easy pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in food processor; process until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Add pumpkin and remaining ingredients; process until combined.
Pour into 9-inch nonstick pie pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let cool.
Cover and refrigerate until firm, at least 5 hours or overnight.
Enjoy! Makes 8 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° or until light brown.

title: braised pork chops with sauerkraut(makes 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have ready the bacon.
Mix it in a casserole with drained sauerkraut, applesauce, brown sugar, water, dry mustard and ground pepper.
Saute gently on both sides the pork chops.
Place them on top of the mixture.
Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: taco squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix sour cream, cheese, mayo and onion. Mix biscuit mix with milk or water until soft dough forms.
Pat dough in pan, pressing dough 1/2-inch up sides.
Layer beef, tomato and green pepper in pan.
Spoon sour cream mixture over top.
Bake until edges of dough are light brown, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bourbon chocolate pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs in a large mixing bowl until frothy.
Add butter, beating well.
Add syrup, sugar, bourbon, flour and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in pecans.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels in pastry shell. Pour pecan mixture over chocolate morsels.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.
Cool before slicing.

title: cheese sauce
directions: In saucepan, melt butter, stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk and stir over low heat until mixture thickens.
Add cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Makes about 3 cups.
Delicious over vegetables.

title: eggplant and shrimp
directions: Saute onions, parsley, green pepper in butter.
Cook eggplant in water until tender.
Drain.
Soak bread in milk.
Add eggplant. Cook celery and tomatoes with sauteed mixture.
Mix with eggplant, shrimp and eggs.
Put in baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs. Cook 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle with cheese and cook until cheese melts.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together soup, sour cream, melted margarine, onion, cheese and seasonings.
Pour over potatoes.
With fork, push sauce into potatoes.
Top with cornflakes.
Drizzle 1/2 cup melted butter over mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: super delight cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix using package directions for a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Cool completely.
Prepare pudding mix using package directions.
Spread over cooled cake. Top with whipped topping. Chill until serving time.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Drain green beans.
Cut each slice of bacon into thirds.
Take 4 green beans and wrap in bacon.
Put in 2 inch deep dish and cover with dressing.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Split squash lengthwise.
Scoop out inside of squash and cook in skillet with the onion, butter and seasonings.
When done, add 1 cup cracker crumbs, beaten eggs and ham.
Stuff filling into shells that have been scalded a few minutes.
Sprinkle rest of finely rolled cracker crumbs and paprika on squash and drip a little butter from pastry brush over top.
Bake in pan with a few drops of water to keep from sticking.
You may sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix the sugar and cornstarch in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in the water gradually.
Cook over medium heat until thick and clear. As the mixture begins to boil, remove the pan from the heat and stir in the gelatin.
When the mixture becomes smooth, add the strawberries.
Pour the filling into the crust and refrigerate until thick.

title: blueberry pandowdy
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, toss blueberries with 2 tablespoons sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In medium-size bowl, combine flour, remaining sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Add egg, milk and butter.
Mix batter until well combined.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix cooked potatoes, sugar, milk, vanilla and cinnamon together.
Add eggs and butter.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake until brown in a 350° oven.
Yield:
7 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cut up fryers and boil in salted water until tender; debone. Save broth. Saute onions, peppers and celery in butter until tender, but not brown. Add soup and tomatoes.
Cook about 20 minutes. Add garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Add cheese until melted. If too dry, add little broth. Cook spaghetti in broth. Add sauce and chicken. Serves 12.

title: ego batter buns
directions: Measure warm water into a large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast. Stir until dissolved.
Stir in sugar, salt and half the flour. Beat with a spoon until smooth.
Add egg and margarine.
Beat in rest of flour until smooth.
Scrape down sides of bowl; cover.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Stir down dough and spoon into 12 large greased muffin cups, filling to 1/2 full.
Again let rise to top of muffin cups (20 to 30 minutes). Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 12 buns.
Very good.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Place in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour until brown.
Bake on bottom rack of oven at 350°.
Turn oven back to 250° after 10 minutes of baking.

title: breakfast enchiladas
directions: Mash the tomatoes. Add garlic and chilies; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Warm the tortillas in a pan.
Fill with scrambled eggs and cover with cheese sauce.

title: rocky road fudge brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
For bars, in a small, heavy saucepan combine butter and chocolate.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat, until melted, 3 to 5 minutes.
Set aside.

title: cake cornbread
directions: Grease sheet pan (8 x 13). Mix all ingredients with mixer. Pour in pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated fish fillets
directions: Cut fish fillets into bite-sized pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over fillets in shallow dish or marinating tray.
Marinate overnight (or up to 4 hours) in refrigerator. Broil in oven for 4 to 6 minutes until fish flakes easily.

title: strawberry layer cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: lindsay meat 'n' cheese pie
directions: Brown meat with green pepper and onion.
Add salt, pepper and favorite seasonings to taste.
Stir in tomato paste and cook 10 minutes, stirring regularly.
Turn meat mixture into baked pie shell.
Cover entire pie with Lindsay pitted ripe olives.
Sprinkle cheese over olives.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix on medium-high speed until smooth and creamy. Use as a sour cream substitute, as a dressing for salad or as a delicious vegetable dip. Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch casserole dish; place apples in and sprinkle spices over apples.
Work together sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake, uncovered, until apples are tender at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: 15 bean soup
directions: Wash soup mix and place in large pot.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans.
Soak overnight; drain.
Add 2 quarts of water, ham hocks, salt, pepper and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil, covered, and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender. Add tomatoes, onion, garlic, hot pepper and lemon juice.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring often.
Remove ham hocks, debone and return to soup.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat baking powder and egg until fluffy.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in 8-inch greased baking pan or a cast-iron skillet, preheated with 1/2 cup shortening in hot 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Mix well and pour into containers and freeze.

title: no-bake cheese cake
directions: Mix together gelatine, sugar and salt in a double boiler. Beat together egg yolks and milk.
Add to gelatine mixture.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until gelatine is dissolved and mixture thickens, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add grated lemon rind.
Cool.
Stir in cottage cheese, lemon juice and vanilla.
Chill, stirring occasionally until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut.
Roll into logs.
Roll logs in coconut.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Slice into cookies. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Use spray oil or shortening on 10-inch tube cake pan and then flour.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, flour and baking powder.
Add to this creamed mixture the milk.
Stir in vanilla, butter, lemon, rum and coconut extracts.
Add chopped nuts, if wanted.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool.
Cake is great with vanilla ice cream.

title: "light raspberry gelatin" dessert
directions: In small bowl mix jello and water; add pineapple.
In a small mold sprayed with Pam, tear or cut angel food cake and arrange cake in mold.
Then pour jello mixture in top.
Refrigerate with a saucer or plate on top to keep cake from floating while the cake and jello set.
Sets in about 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Crush blueberries.
Add sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Mix well. Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add vanilla.
Serve over pancakes or blintzes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump into a 13 x 9-inch pan (do not grease) in order listed. Crumble dry cake mix over fruit.
Sprinkle coconut or chopped walnuts over cake mix.
Melt butter and drizzle over top.
Bake 1 hour in 325° to 350° oven.
Serve cake from the pan with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, salt, vegetable oil, vanilla, cinnamon and soda.
Add flour and mix.
Add apples, carrots, pecans and coconut; mix.
Drop in muffin pan that has muffin cup liners.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 48 muffins.
Freezes well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Slice 1/2-inch width top off the top of the angel food ring. Tunnel all the cake out, leaving 1/2 inch (approximately) on bottom and edges of cake ring.
Rip up the cake into bite size pieces.

title: chicken noodles casserole
directions: Prepare the noodles according to the directions on the package.
Mix and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese together until smooth.
Add 1 egg and 1 cup of sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Add 1 egg and 1 cup of flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add 1 egg and 1 cup of sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Add 1 egg and 1 cup of flour.
Mix until smooth. Add 1 egg and 1 cup of sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Add 1 egg and 1 cup of flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add vanilla.

title: brown sugar syrup
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a boil.
Serve over waffles or pancakes.

title: olivia's applesauce cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg. Take 1/2 cup of the flour mix and stir into the nuts and raisins. Set both aside. Cream the butter until whipped soft.
Add sugar, a little at a time, until mixture is smooth. Beat eggs vigorously. Alternately stir in flour mixture and applesauce.
When all is mixed together, add nuts and raisins.
Mix well.
Pour batter into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes, then turn out on cake rack. Frost with Whiskey Frosting when cake is cool.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Peel and slice zucchini (saute fry in butter just to soften). Place in bottom of baking dish.
Fry hamburger and place on top of zucchini slices.
Cover with Ragu sauce.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spareribs and kraut
directions: Brown ribs in hot fat in a Dutch oven.
Add onion, salt, pepper and water.
Cover; simmer for 1 hour.
Add sauerkraut; cover.
Cook 20 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: brazil nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and line with wax paper.
Combine nuts, dates and cherries in a large bowl.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add to nut mixture.
Mix well to coat nuts and fruit and to distribute flour evenly.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat in vanilla.
Add to nut mixture and stir well.
Turn into pan and spread evenly. Bake 1 hour 45 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 or 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and peel off paper.
Cake must be cold before slicing. Makes 3 pound cake.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Add milk and water.
Cook over medium/high heat.
Stir until it starts to thicken.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.

title: cheesy corn pudding
directions: Mix sugar, corn, cornstarch and seasoning.
Beat eggs and milk; stir into corn.
Cook green pepper and onion into oleo until tender.
Add to corn mixture.
Stir in the grated cheese. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: gilbert's favorite libby's famous pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add pumpkin, sugar, salt, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix well.
Add canned milk, a little at a time.
Stir well.
Pour mixture into deep unbaked pie shell.

title: quick chicken soup
directions: *Can be done the night before.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together; let set.
After adding oil, egg and vanilla to apples, add flour, soda and salt.
Mix.
Add 1/2 cup nuts and 1/2 cup coconut.
Mix.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: fruit cake(icebox)
directions: Crumble crackers and add nuts, raisins, cherries, pineapple and coconut after ingredients have been chopped.
Melt marshmallows, milk and butter in double boiler.
Pour over mixture and mix thoroughly.
Pour into buttered pan and set in icebox. Keep refrigerated.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In small pan combine water, cubes and broccoli.
Cover and cook until tender.
Saute onions in butter: add flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Cook until thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add broccoli mixture and cook on low heat for 1/2 hour.

title: summer delight
directions: Place cottage cheese in bowl and sprinkle jello on top.
Blend well.
Mix in Cool Whip, pineapple and orange sections.
Pour into mold or pretty glass bowl.
Best refrigerated overnight.

title: bran flake cookie
directions: Cream oleo and sugars; add oil, then egg and flavorings. Follow with dry ingredients and milk.
Drop by teaspoon and bake at 350° until light brown, 8 to 9 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Clean and cut up broccoli.
Add first 7 ingredients in a large saucepan; cook on low heat.
Stir occasionally.
Boil broccoli for 12 minutes or until tender and immediately add to mixture. Increase heat to medium-high.
Simmer and stir.
Melt butter; mix with flour to get creamy mixture.
Add to soup.
When soup thickens, add sherry.
Mix well.
Eat.

title: blue-cheesed flounder
directions: Place flounder fillets, lemon juice, onion, parsley and water in pressure cooker.
Close cover securely.
Place pressure regulator on vent pipe.
Cook 5 minutes.
Cool pressure cooker at once.
Stir in cream and blue cheese.
Heat through.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked clam dip
directions: In a deep bowl pour clams with juice, add butter.
Crush one package of crackers at a time.
Best way to do this is to crush them in a plastic bag.
Add to mixture.
Add to mixture the following:
lemon juice, parsley, oregano and garlic.
Mix well with fork.
Pour into deep baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake.
After 20 minutes, mix with fork and sprinkle the left over cheese and more if you need it.
Serve on Ritz crackers.
Do not cover.

title: recipe for love
directions: Take a man and a woman; add lips pressed together.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups teasing, blend in 2 cups squeezing.
Sift in moonlight to taste.
Then add 2 more squeezes and 1 1/2 cups more teasing. Stir in 6 cups love.
Simmer for life.

title: curly pasta salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, cheese and milk and set aside.
Mix other ingredients and add dressing mixture.
Let set overnight and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Mix 1/3 cup cocoa mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Bake in oven at 400° until tender and done or throw in crock-pot for 4 hours.

title: green broccoli salad
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise.
Toss all together.

title: chili egg puffs
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese, jack cheese and melted butter.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in chilies.
Pour mixture into well buttered pan (9x13x2).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken 1 1/2 hours.
Cut shortening into flour.
Remove chicken from broth.
Pour 1/3 cup broth into shortening and flour. Boil remaining broth.
Add ice water to flour mixture until it makes a thick ball.
Salt and pepper broth to taste.
Roll dough out 1/8 inch.
(Note: Harder the dough, better the dumpling.)
Cut dumplings in strips and put in broth.
Boil 8 minutes.
Pick chicken off bone and put in broth.
Do not stir chicken to bottom. Cook until chicken is warm.

title: czechoslovakian cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add egg yolks; mix until blended.
Slowly add flour and nuts; mix until blended.
Spoon 1/2 of the nut mixture into 8-inch square pan; spread evenly.
Cover mixture in pan with jam and pat remaining mixture over jam, covering jam completely.
Put in a cold oven; turn oven on to 325° and bake for 1 hour.

title: russian piroshki(spring rolls)
directions: Saute onion and cabbage in butter until onion is tender, about 3 minutes.
Add beef; cook, breaking up with a wooden spoon until no pink remains.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Stir in eggs, dill, sour cream and salt; mix well.
(Makes about 2 cups filling.) Divide filling evenly among 8 spring roll wrappers.
Fold bottom of wrapper over filling; fold in both sides, then fold down top, completely enclosing filling.
Pour enough oil into a large saucepan to make a 2 inch depth.
Heat to 375 degrees on a deep-fat frying thermometer.
Deep-fry spring rolls, turning often, until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve with dollop of sour cream.

title: apple dumpling cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Grease bottom only of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread apples and raisins evenly over bottom of cake pan. In a large bowl, combine cake mix, 1/2 cup water, margarine, sour cream and eggs at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed. Spoon batter evenly over fruit in pan.

title: picnic potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins for 20 minutes.
Cool, peel and shred potatoes.
Saute onions in margarine until tender.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Mix potatoes with cheese; add soup mixture.
Turn into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender. Mix 2 cups hot cooked rice with Cheez Whiz. Add remaining ingredients and pour into a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin-oatmeal cookies
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets with a little bit of shortening.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies until you have coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
To the rest, add the melted butter and mix well. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Cream the cheese with electric mixer, adding powdered sugar; beat well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread mixture on top of crust, reserving 1 cup for later. Let chill 30 minutes.

title: christmas breakfast
directions: Put bread pieces in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook and drain sausage and add.
Then add cheese and green chilies.
Mix the other ingredients together and pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar (gradually).
Blend in peanut butter and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 3 minutes after each one with electric beater on medium speed.
Turn into bake pie shell and chill at least 2 hours.
When ready to serve, top with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Stir well and bake in crust until done, about 30 minutes. Bake at 300° to 350°, depending on your oven.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Add milk, then blend in Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into pie crust and refrigerate 4 hours before serving.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together.
Keep in tightly closed jar.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in large casserole dish; mix well. Cook in 350° oven until cabbage and rice are well done.

title: waldord astaris cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla; fold in dry ingredients. Mix well!
Pour into two greased and floured cake pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: scalloped corn and oysters
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish.
Cover with crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine first seven ingredients in a large bowl; add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir until well blended.	Prepare pans for baking and bake at 350°.
If using round pans, bake 25 minutes; if using a 9 x 13-inch pan, bake for 35 minutes.

title: clam cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients except shortening together.
Batter should be moist.
Heat Crisco in deep fryer or large electric frying pan. Be sure shortening is very hot, about 400°.
Drop batter by heaping teaspoonfuls into hot shortening.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Each clam cake should have room to turn over on its own when cooking.
Pan should be large enough to cook 6 to 10 clam cakes at one time. Remove cooked clam cakes from shortening and drain on paper towel. Yields 3 to 4 dozen cakes.

title: eye of round roast
directions: Season roast well with seasoning salt.
Place fat side up on rack of shallow baking pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 45 minutes.
Do not cover.
Do not add water.

title: chocolate-covered turtle cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder; set aside. Cream together the butter and brown sugar in a bowl until light and fluffy, using electric mixer at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

Beat in vanilla. Gradually stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture, mixing well. Arrange pecan halves in clusters of 4, about 2 inches apart, on ungreased baking sheets, placing halves in the form of a cross. Drop dough, by rounded teaspoonfuls, in center of each cluster. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove from baking sheets; cool in racks.
Prepare Chocolate Icing. Makes 40.

title: pot roast dinner
directions: Cover roast with foil and bake in oven until almost done, about 2 hours.
Peel potatoes and cut into wedges.
Slice carrots and onion.
Take roast out of oven and place potatoes, carrots and onions on top of roast and around sides.
Pour lima beans on top. Cover and cook another hour.
Bake at 350°.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix sugar with potatoes.
Add shortening and beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients to potato mixture alternately with milk.
Roll out on floured board; cut and place in a greased baking pan.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Place stew meat in bottom of casserole or 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add vegetables.
Mix tapioca, sugar, salt and pepper together.
Sprinkle this mixture over vegetables.
Pour 1 cup tomato juice (or a little more) over all.
Cover tightly with foil. Cook 5 to 6 hours in a 325° oven.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon holiday ornaments(non-edible!)
directions: Mix to form a dough.
Keep dough in fridge 2 hours.
Sprinkle cinnamon on board and knead dough to smooth.
Roll on board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into shapes with cookie cutters.
Punch a hole in top of each shape with a straw.
Dry for 4 days, turning each day or bake 2 hours in a warm oven.
Use a ribbon to hang. Decorate with paint, buttons, ribbon, etc.

title: mrs. dudley hughes' lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into uncooked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake and crumble it into 1 to 2-inch pieces.
Put layer of cake in the bottom of a punch bowl.
Make pudding and pour over cake.
Sprinkle about 1/3 of the coconut on top of the pudding. Sprinkle about 1/3 pecans on top of coconut.

title: orange yogurt jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in yogurt until dissolved.	When slightly
jelled,	stir
in fruit.
Pour into mold or fancy bowl and refrigerate until firm.

title: oriental beef stir-fry
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook peppers, leeks and artichoke hearts in 3 teaspoons hot oil.
Cook, stirring constantly, 2 to 3 minutes until just tender-crisp.
With slotted spoon, remove from skillet; set aside.
In same skillet, add remaining 2 teaspoons oil, soy sauce and honey; heat.
Add beef. Cool, stirring constantly, 2 to 3 minutes until cooked through. Return vegetables to skillet.
Add sesame seeds; toss to coat evenly.
Serves 4.

title: saucy spareribs
directions: Sprinkle spareribs with half of the salt on both sides. Broil 10 minutes on one side, turn and broil 10 minutes on the other side or until brown.
Remove from broiler and pour off fat. Sprinkle ribs with remaining salt.
Place ribs in a single layer in pan or on a cookie sheet and bake uncovered for 20 - 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Meanwhile, combine applesauce, syrup, paprika and cloves.
Spoon this on ribs and bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: tropical tuna melt
directions: Thoroughly drain the pineapple, reserving 1 teaspoon juice. Stir together reserved juice, salad dressing and mustard.
In a small bowl, stir together the drained pineapple, tuna and celery. Stir in salad dressing mixture.
Arrange toasted muffins in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top each muffin half with some tuna mixture. Cut cheese in half diagonally.
Top each muffin with a cheese triangle.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 to 2 minutes. Rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Microwave for 1 to 2 minutes more. Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberries
directions: Shape and roll in jello.
Use #66 tube for leaves.

title: cinnamon krisp
directions: Cream butter and shortening. Add eggs and brown sugar. Stir. Add flour and cinnamon, butter, and baking soda, mix well. Stir in corn flakes. Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Cook at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Fry and chop the sausage.
Add flour and brown.
If sausage is dry, you may need to add shortening when adding flour.
Add salt and pepper; stir well.
Add milk; heat to boiling point and reduce heat.
Simmer for a few minutes, stirring constantly.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 quarts gravy.

title: pumpkin holiday pie*
directions: Stir cream cheese until soft.
Add dry milk, sugar substitute and vanilla.
Blend in 1/2 cup whipped topping.
Spread evenly over bottom of crust.
In medium bowl, combine evaporated skim milk, canned pumpkin and pie spice.
Add dry pudding mix.
Mix well, using wire whisk.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill until set.
Top with whipped topping before serving.

title: egg custard
directions: Put all in blender and mix well, approximately 3 minutes. Pour in greased, floured baking dish and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Let set in dish about 5 minutes until bubbles settle down. Sprinkle top with nutmeg.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruit except banana and kiwi. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
One hour before serving, add kiwi and banana.
Serves 15.

title: apple fritters
directions: Prepare Coating Batter.
Peel and core a large apple.
Slice thinly and dip in batter.
Cook in deep fat, smoking hot.
Drain fritters on paper towels to absorb some of the excess fat and enjoy them sprinkled with sugar.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dump all in one bowl and mix.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine the ingredients into a large bowl; best tools are washed hands for mixing. Shape mixed ingredients into a well-greased loaf pan (iron skillets are much better). Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes. About halfway through, add by smoothing tomato paste on top. Yields about 8 servings.

title: turkey cups(makes 10 cups. prep. time 10 minutes. cook time, 25 minutes.)
directions: 1) Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In
muffin pans, press one biscuit onto bottom and sides of each cup. Chill until ready to fill.

title: b and b pickled eggs
directions: Bring all ingredients, except eggs, to a boil.
In a sealable jar, pour over peeled eggs.
Let sit for 3 days to 3 months.
Shake once a day.
Serve with salt, pepper and Tabasco.

title: valentine honey hearts(easy)
directions: Mix butter and honey.
Add oats, dry milk and water.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Roll dough 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with heart-shaped cookie cutter.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake in tube pan for 45 minutes or until done.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add bananas and milk. Mix good and add eggs, flour, soda, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Fold in chopped nuts.

title: salsa
directions: Chop all ingredients and mix well.
Other ingredients may be added, or subtracted, according to taste. If too hot, add a little water and more tomatoes.

title: irish bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add egg and beat.
Add dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Fold in sour cream, raisins and caraway seed.
Put in a greased pie pan (9-inch).
Make a cross on top of bread or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: roast(as used at amish weddings)
directions: Roast chickens in oven until done.
Remove meat from bones and cube.
Set aside.
Mix butter, margarine and ground celery in saucepan and cook until butter browns.
Set aside.
Beat eggs; add seasonings.
Pour over bread cubes.
Add butter mixture and toss. Place in greased roast pan.
Cover and bake at 250° for 1 hour or until done.
Stir a few times so edges don't dry out.
Serve with chicken gravy.

title: giant pretzels
directions: Grease 2 large baking sheets.
In large bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in sugar, salt and enough flour until soft and sticky dough forms.
Turn dough onto well floured board.
Knead dough for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cut in half, then cut each half into 6 pieces.
Roll out and make pretzel shape. Mix together egg and water; brush on pretzels.
Sprinkle with salt. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy, then mix in remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup each of both cheeses.
Transfer mixture to casserole and sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers in jars.
Add clove of garlic, dill, red pepper and 1/8 teaspoon of powdered alum to each jar and seal.

title: emma's potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes while warm in small pieces.
Salt and pepper the potatoes.
Add other ingredients.

title: annie's dilled cucumbers
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk in saucepan over very low heat, stirring, until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat.
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk until well blended.
Refrigerate to cool, about 10 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping, blending until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Garnish with chocolate curls.
Store leftover covered in freezer.
"My kind of recipe, nice and easy."

title: no cook coconut pie
directions: Beat pudding, milk and coconut flavoring until combined.
Then beat on high for 2 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping and flaked coconut.
Pour into crust.
Brown some coconut in butter on top of stove.
Sprinkle on top of pie.
Chill until serving time.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix 1 stick melted margarine, potatoes, sour cream, undiluted chicken soup, onions, Cheddar cheese, salt and pepper.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with topping made with crushed corn flakes and 1 stick melted margarine.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: great-grandma's potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes, cut into eighths and boil until tender in salted water.
Drain and cool.
Hard-boil eggs, cool and peel. Place potatoes and eggs in a large bowl and mash well by hand with a potato masher, but not as thoroughly as in preparing mashed potatoes.
Chop fine and add onion, celery and sweet peppers.
Add dressing, salt and pepper to taste.
The mashed potatoes absorb a lot of dressing, so before serving, check to see if more dressing is needed.
Keep refrigerated. Serves about 6.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into oblong baking dish. Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: beef brisket in beer
directions: Trim excess fat from brisket.
Place meat in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with onion slices.
In bowl, combine chili sauce, brown sugar, garlic and beer.
Pour over meat.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 3 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more, basting occasionally with juices.
Remove meat to platter. Skim excess fat from drippings.
Measure liquid and add water to make 1 cup.
Blend flour and 1/2 cup water combined with drippings. Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 375° for 50 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out each potato, leaving thin shell.
Place scooped potato in mixing bowl; add cream cheese, chives, basil, salt and pepper.
Beat until smooth.
Add milk, one tablespoon at a time, until fluffy.
Spoon potatoes into shells. Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cut zucchini in half; thinly slice zucchini, onion and red pepper.
Seed and chop tomato.
Seed jalapeno and cut into thin strips.
Cut corn from cob into a bowl; add zucchini, onion, red pepper, tomato, jalapeno, ranch dressing, salt and pepper.
Toss to coat.
Cover and chill at least 4 hours.
Cut yellow peppers in half lengthwise; discard seeds and membrane.
Stuff with vegetable mixture.
Serves 4.

title: world's best peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugars and eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Mix the flour, soda, powder and salt together, then pour into fluffy mixture.
Stir the two very well.
Spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Crisscross with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Stir and refreeze.

title: cream eggs and tuna on toast
directions: Boil eggs.
Crack and smash eggs.
Melt butter, add flour. Stir until thickens.
Add milk, stir.
Add tuna.
Add the eggs. Stir until thickens.
Put on toast.

title: quick steak divine
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
Rub with salt, pepper, Kitchen Bouquet and Worcestershire sauce.
Place in an iron skillet with 1/3 cup water and several pats butter.
Top with onions and bell peppers.
Cover and cook until tender, about 1 1/2 or 2 hours. For a complete meal, add potatoes and carrots.

title: reelfoot lake pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients and use as needed.
When rolling and preparing any pastry or pie crust, handle as little as possible to ensure flakiness and to prevent toughness.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop from tablespoon into hot cooking oil.
Fry until lightly brown.
Drain.

title: cold banana pudding
directions: Mix the instant pudding with 2 cups milk and can of Eagle Brand with a whisk for approximately 2 minutes. Let set.

title: sour cream cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers. Add salt and let set for 10 to 15 minutes. Drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill.

title: cheesy potatoes and franks
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in hot Crisco until tender.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk.
Cook and stir over low heat until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese and mustard.
Cut hot dogs into 1/4-inch slices.
In greased 2-quart casserole, arrange layers of half the potatoes, hot dogs and cheese sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: walnut pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs in large bowl; add sugar, syrup, butter and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in walnuts and pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 35 minutes or until center is firm.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place brisket on long sheets of heavy duty tinfoil crossed in roasting pan.
Put tenderizer and garlic powder on both sides of beef and prick meat with a fork.
In a bowl, mix salad dressing, onion soup, gravy and mushrooms.
Pour over meat.
Loosely cover and seal edges of tin foil lightly.
You may want a second cover of foil to doubly secure.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour per pound.
Cool with tin foil opened and slice when completely cool.

title: mints
directions: Mix together and roll out.
Cut into small pieces.
Put food color in if you wish.

title: lucy's icebox rolls
directions: Combine shortening and boiling water.
Stir until fat melts. Add egg, sugar and salt.
Beat in cold water.
Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine mixture and flour.
