Cover with damp cloth and chill overnight.
Next day, shape and let rise in a warm place for 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: microwave peanut brittle #2
directions: Place sugar, peanuts and corn syrup in a large microwave-safe dish.
Cook on High in microwave for 4 minutes and 15 seconds. Stir.
Cook another 4 minutes and 15 seconds.
Stir and add vanilla and margarine.
Cook for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Add soda.
Stir well.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet; spread and pull quickly until thin and let it cool.
Break into pieces and store in a sealed container.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill 6 hours.
Serve with chips or raw veggies.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Cut cabbage, add salt and let stand 1 hour.
Then squeeze out all excess water or mixture, add other ingredients.

title: fruit salad
directions: Stir fruit together and then add nuts, coconut and marshmallows.
Fold in 6 ounces of Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: hot chicken casserole(on the light side)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute onions and peppers in nonstick skillet sprayed with nonstick spray.
Add tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 4 minutes, until blended.
Add chopped cheese, stirring until melted.
Add chicken, mushrooms and peas.
Add vermicelli to mixture; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into casserole dish that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Heat until bubbly.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown sausage and onions until done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes or until thick.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: In double boiler, melt margarine; add flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until mixture is smooth and creamy, stirring often.
Let dip "sit" for a few hours before serving for a spicier flavor.
Serve warm.

title: pizza crescent bake
directions: Unroll 1 tube of crescent rolls; place in lightly greased 9 x 13 baking pan. Press to seal perforations. Brown ground beef; drain. Sprinkle over dough. Top with pizza sauce and sprinkle with cheese. Unroll remaining crescent roll dough and place over cheese; seal on sides. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Saute celery and onion in oleo.
Mix mushroom soup and 3/4 can milk with sauteed celery and onions. Add cooked rice and broccoli.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Grease a 2-quart casserole with oleo.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Add strawberries and pineapple; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Put in loaf pan and freeze.
Take out of freezer 1 hour before serving.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Mix well.
Make into balls the size of a nickel or so.
Put into mini muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Take out and immediately place miniature Reese's cup in center of each.
Let cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Makes 80 to 100 pieces.

title: morning glory bran muffins
directions: Mix oil and all-bran; set aside.
Mix in large bowl flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in carrots, raisins and apples.
Beat eggs and add vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Add oil and all-bran.
Spoon into buttered muffin tins or use paper liners. Fill to top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: snow cream
directions: Have fun gathering 1 large bowl of snow.
Beat the egg.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Combine with snow and add milk for consistency.
Enjoy!

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients together until ice cubes are dissolved.

title: swiss chocolate
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding mix in bowl (dry).
Add eggs, milk and oil, blending until moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into 3 round, greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, cream and butter to a slow boil.
Once boiling, let boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Pour into prepared platters (buttered).
Cut when cooled.

title: party cheese ball
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cream cheese and cheddar cheese. Blend in mayonnaise, worcestershire sauce, celery salt and garlic salt.
Stir in olives and onion.
Cover, chill 2 - 3 hours for flavor to blend.
When ready to serve, shape cream cheese mixture into ball, roll in pecans to coat.
Serve with crackers.

title: italian escarole soup
directions: Boil chicken.
After the chicken is finished remove from the broth and cut it in tiny pieces.
Cook the escarole separate and after it is cooked cut in small pieces and put in the broth.
Add the chicken pieces and little meatballs into the broth.
After about an hour, beat the eggs and cheese in a separate dish.
With fork, mix the eggs and cheese into the soup.
Let it cook for 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until well mixed.
Add flour, baking powder and pudding mix and beat until smooth.
Add apples, nuts and dates and stir gently until well mixed.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: cheese and onion soup
directions: Melt butter in double boiler over direct heat.
Add onions, cooking over low heat until almost tender.
Place over pan of boiling water, gradually adding flour, then milk.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add seasonings and cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Sprinkle parsley on top to serve.
Serves 4.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix sour cream with granulated sugar.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, add frozen coconut, crumbled up.
Then bake a yellow cake (brand name of your choice) the kind that uses butter not oil, according to package directions.
Spread into 2 greased and floured round cake pans and bake according to package directions.
Split 2 layers into 4 layering cake, filling and alternating until all layers and filling are used, ending with filling on top.
Then use thawed Cool Whip to frost top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle thawed coconut package on top and sides of cake.
Cover and refrigerate for 5 days before serving.
The longer the cake sits in the refrigerator, the moister it becomes.

title: lettuce, pea and egg salad
directions: Toss all together.
When ready to serve, add the slaw dressing and toss again.

title: french silk pie
directions: Beat sugar and 3/4 cup butter for 4 minutes.
Next, melt 3 tablespoons butter and cocoa.
Let cool, then stir into sugar/butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating mixture 1 minute after each egg, scraping sides of bowl well.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Garnish with chocolate curls.

title: gloria's chicken
directions: Combine all the soups. Add rice, water and mushrooms.
Reserve a cup of mixture and set aside.
Place mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan and set chicken on top of mixture.
Pour reserved liquid over chicken and dab butter on top.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Prebake pie dough in pie pan.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour in pie pan, then bake at 375° (after placing strips of dough on top of pie).

title: pound cake
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder and sift 3 times. Cream butter, sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well. Add
flour	and
milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavorings.
Cook in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.
It may need to cook 5 or 10 minutes longer.

title: mike's mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and season with chili powder.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Spread refried beans in pan.
Layer 1/2 of ground meat, chips, 1/2 cheese, all of sour cream, remaining meat and chips.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and browned.

title: sauerkraut cocoa cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with water.
Beat well after each addition.
Drain and chop sauerkraut.
Stir into batter.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until done when tested.

title: chicken chimichangas
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in 12-inch skillet to medium-high. Brown chicken, onion and pepper.
Add olives, chili powder, cumin, garlic, salt and pepper to taste and sage, stirring constantly. Cook until vegetables are tender.
Stir in water/cornstarch mixture.
Stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the hamburger in a skillet; drain.
Drain the tomatoes; reserve the juice, then cut up the tomatoes.
Add the tomatoes, cheese, lettuce and onions to the hamburger.
Combine the reserved tomato juice, hot sauce and beans; simmer until heated through. Add to the hamburger mixture; toss well.
Add the corn chips, salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.

title: sam's favorite cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries in the food processor.
Add sugar.
Let set in the refrigerator overnight.
Drain well.
Add other ingredients.

title: corn pudding
directions: Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Add zucchini.
Add nuts and raisins. Grease and flour bread pan.
Bake at 300°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes for large bread pan.
May use smaller pans.
Observe as bakes to adjust baking time.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Take chicken off bones and place in casserole dish.
Melt the margarine.
Add soup and milk.
Pour over chicken in casserole dish.
Mix stuffing with broth.
Spoon over mixture.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; mix in oil and vanilla.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Stir in zucchini.
Coat nuts and raisins with small amount of flour.
Stir into batter.
Bake in Bundt pan or 2 loaves at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: cheddar crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease large baking sheet.
Set aside. In large bowl, stir together flour, cornmeal, baking soda, sugar and salt.
Using a pastry blender, cut butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Using fork, stir in shredded cheese, cold water and vinegar just until mixture forms soft dough. If necessary, knead mixture in bowl until smooth.
Shape dough into ball.
Wrap ball with plastic wrap and refrigerate about 1 hour or until it's firm enough to handle.
On lightly floured surface, use a floured rolling pin to roll 1/4 of dough into a paper thin round, diameter 13-inches.
Keep remaining dough refrigerated.
Using fluted pastry cutter or pizza cutter, cut into 8 wedges.
Transfer onto prepared baking sheets.
Sprinkle with black pepper.
Bake until browned and crisped, 8 to 10 minutes.
After cooled, store in tight container.
Repeat with rest of dough.

title: souffle au chocolat
directions: In saucepan, combine chocolate and confectioners sugar. Gradually add warm milk, stirring constantly.
Place over low heat and stir until mixture reaches the boiling point.
Remove from heat and stir in softened gelatin, granulated sugar, vanilla and salt.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat with rotary beater until light and fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into a 2-quart serving dish and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pecan pie(never fails)
directions: Cream the oleo and brown sugar together until fluffy.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Line pie pan with pastry and sprinkle with pecans.
Pour filling over pecans. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Check about 50 minutes and determine if center is firm.
If not, cook the other 10 or 15 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix
ingredients in order given.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
While cake is still hot, pour sauce over it.

title: pineapple - cheerwine punch
directions: Chill punch bowl.
When ready to serve, pour slush (pineapple juice) into punch bowl.
Add Cheerwines and mix.
Great taste and easy.
Makes approximately 24 servings.

title: dino's italian meat sauce
directions: Saute meat; pour off fat and set aside.
Saute vegetables and garlic in olive oil.
Add meat, tomatoes, puree and paste.
Season to taste.
Simmer until flavors blend, 1 to 3 hours.
Serve over pasta; sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: party pleasers
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage, drain well and return to pan. Add velveeta and oregano, mix well. Stir until cheese is melted. Spread on rye bread slices. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, including sugar, into bowl. Make a well and add other ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into 3 medium size greased and floured loaf pans or 1 loaf pan and 1 (9 to 10-inch) angel food pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until done in 350° oven.
Remove from pan and place on rack to cool.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar for 20 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat for 5 minutes each time.
Add flour and lemon extract.
Beat until blended.
Fold in 7-Up.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
May sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll in small balls.
Place in shallow pan (don't brown meat balls).

title: chicken and green bean casserole
directions: Butter medium size casserole dish.
Add green beans and chicken.
Beat
soup
and
milk;
pour over chicken and beans. Mix bread cubes,
butter and cheese.
Put this over the casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit and pasta salad
directions: Finely shred enough orange peel to make 1/2 teaspoon; set aside.
Remove the remaining peel from orange and section orange over a bowl to catch juice.
Measure 2 tablespoons of the juice. In a medium mixing bowl, stir together orange peel, the 2 tablespoons juice, the yogurt, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Add cooked pasta, chopped apples and sliced green onions; toss to coat.
Gently stir in orange sections.
Cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Bring water to a boil and add 1 teaspoon salt. Add macaroni and cook 10 minutes.

title: "pile o candy"(chocolate or maple fudge)
directions: Cook sugar, milk and chocolate until soft ball will form in cold water. Add butter and vanilla. Beat with electric mixer until it begins to get firm (watch closely!). Add pecans and stir slowly or it will harden fast. Pour in a big pile. Do not spread out. Pour onto wax paper and cut as needed.

title: freezing corn
directions: Mix and boil for 20 minutes.
Cool and put in freezer.

title: amy's chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender; stir in broth.
Pick chicken off bones.
Set aside.
Melt margarine.
Mix with stuffing.
Mix soup with 1 can of juice from chicken.
Keep separate.
In a casserole dish, layer stuffing, chicken soup, until everything is used with stuffing.
Bake on 400° until top brown.

title: blueberry conserve
directions: Bring
sugar
and
water
to
boil in a large pan.
Add orange and lemon and cook for 5 minutes.	Add blueberries and cook
for 40 to 60 minutes or until mixture begins to thicken. Pour
into 1/2
pint
jars
and
seal	with
metal ring lids. Process	in boiling
water bath for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 (1/2 pint) jars.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles according to package; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Be sure you beat the eggs.
Put cinnamon on top of ingredients.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour or more; put knife in center.
When it comes out clean, it's done.

title: snickerdoodle biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

Lightly spoon flour into dry measuring cups and level with a knife. Combine flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl. Combine oil, vanilla and eggs; add to flour mixture, stirring until well-blended (dough will be dry and crumbly). Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 7 to 8 times. Divide the dough in half. Shape each portion into an 8 inch long roll. Place rolls 6 inches apart on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray, and flatten each roll to one inch thickness. Combine 2 Tbsp. sugar and 1 tsp. cinnamon. Gently brush tops of rolls with egg white and sprinkle with the cinnamon mixture.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain grease.
Combine ground beef, Ragu sauce and sugar in pan.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, cover bottom with sauce, layer of noodles, sauce and cheese.
Add another layer of noodles, sauce and cheeses. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cracklin' bread
directions: Mix the ingredients and bake in medium tins, corn stick pan or baking pan.
This is a Georgia Agrirama recipe.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Put carrots, celery, onion, water and bouillon cubes into blender container.
Cover and process at "grind" until vegetables are finely chopped.
Pour into saucepan; cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Put milk, flour and cheese into blender container.
Cover and process at "liquefy" until mixture is smooth. Stir in vegetable mixture and cook until thickened.

title: banana punch
directions: Food process all fruits, juice and lemonade.
Pour into Ziploc bags and freeze.

title: mock toffee
directions: Boil butter and sugar for 3 minutes.
On a large cookie sheet, place saltines in a single layer.
Pour mixture over them.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes (watch carefully).
Spread chocolate chips over and spread them as they melt.
Chill.
Break into pieces.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce together and spread into 9-inch pie plate.
Mix cocktail sauce and horseradish together and spread on top of cream cheese.
Break up pieces of crabmeat and put on top of sauce.
Sprinkle chopped parsley over top.
Serve with crackers.

title: meatballs
directions: Soak 8 slices bread in water.
Squeeze out moisture.
Combine soaked bread with all other ingredients.
Form into balls.
Brown slowly in 3 to 4 tablespoon salad oil.
Simmer in your favorite sauce.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix and add 1 egg at a time.
Beat after each egg.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool 15 minutes.
Mix xxxx sugar with juice of lemon or use lemon icing.
Pour over cake while it's still warm.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: In a shallow pan, beat egg and milk.
Dip each pork chop in the mixture, then coat with cracker crumbs, patting to make a thick coating.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Cook pork chop uncovered, for about 8-10 minutes per side or until browned and juices run clear. Yield 3-6 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Put into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in 350°
oven for 35 minutes.
Leave cake in pan.

title: amish oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Let set for 2 hours, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Put the oatmeal in mixing bowl. Add butter and boiling water. Let stand 20 minutes. Stir until all oatmeal is wet.
Add the eggs, brown sugar and white sugar.
Sift the flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt. Sift this into the first mixture.
Mix well and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato (indian) relish
directions: Skin and chop tomatoes.
Peel, core and chop apples.
Chop onions.
Coarsely chop red pepper.
Put all ingredients in kettle. Heat to boiling point and then simmer 3 to 4 hours, stirring frequently.
Bottle and seal in sterilized jars.

title: all-purpose salad dressing
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Serve with lettuce or slaw or on potato salad.
May omit milk; I do.

title: tennessee pineapple surprise
directions: In casserole dish, mix together pineapple with juice, cornstarch and sugar. In medium bowl, mix together crackers, Cheddar cheese and melted butter. Pour dry ingredients on top of pineapple mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. If a double batch, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna-broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soup and salad dressing; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients except shoestring potatoes.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.

title: chess squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cake mix and softened butter.
Add one egg.
Press mixture into rectangle baking pan to form a crust.
Cream the cream cheese and add eggs, slightly beaten, 1 at a time to cream cheese.
Add confectioners sugar to mixture.
(Save 5 teaspoons out.) Pour mixture over crust and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Dust lightly with remaining confectioners sugar.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse and drain.
Put chopped tomatoes in bottom of pot and add spaghetti.
Mix well and add salt.
Place a layer into baking dish.
Top with cheese slices and layer again with spaghetti and cheese.
Pour milk over spaghetti and sprinkle with corn flake crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Pour over crackers.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Keep tightly covered.

title: apples "n" rice casserole(yields 4 servings)
directions: Place butter in 1-quart casserole dish.
Heat in microwave on Full power for 20 to 30 seconds or until melted.
Stir in rice, apples, lemon juice, sugar, cinnamon and sour cream.
Bake in microwave, covered, on Full power for 4 1/2 to 5 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: pizza crescent bake
directions: Unroll one tube of crescent dough; place in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Press to seal perforations.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare vegetables according to directions on package.
Drain. In a pan, heat soup, cream cheese and Cheddar cheese until sauce is smooth and cheese is melted.
Combine vegetables and sauce; add mushrooms and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place corn flakes and spices in plastic storage bag and crush with rolling pin. Sprinkle crushed flakes on top of casserole and drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until sauce bubbles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chorizo beans
directions: Any amount pinto beans and chorizo sausage desired; ratio is 1:4 sausage to beans.

title: 24-hour omelet
directions: Butter bread and cut in 1-inch cubes; place in a 9 x 13-inch dish with buttered sides up.
Beat eggs with milk and seasoning. Pour over bread, then put ham on top and cheese as final layer. Cover with tinfoil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can be prepared 24 hours ahead of time and kept in refrigerator until time to be baked.

title: adelaide's old-fashioned vegetable soup
directions: Salt and pepper turkey necks to taste.
Cut onions over necks and cook in about 2 cups of water until tender, about 1 hour. Add ketchup and other vegetables, one at a time, until dissolved. Add more water if sauce is too thick.

title: bake ahead breakfast
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Tear bread into little pieces and place in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Sprinkle cooked sausage over bread.
Mix eggs, milk, cheese, salt and mustard.
Pour over sausage. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bean medley
directions: Put all ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for one hour, stirring frequently.
Add water if necessary.

title: fried dill pickles
directions: Put the cornmeal and the flour in a bowl.
Sprinkle a good bit of Creole seasoning on top of it.
Put grease in the skillet and let the grease get hot.
Dip the pickles in the bowl and fry them until they float on the top.

title: baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken in tomato sauce.
Coat with crushed corn flakes. Place in greased baking dish with about 1 inch between each chicken breast.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Check to see if chicken is done.

title: picante black bean soup
directions: Cook bacon in 3-quart saucepan until crisp.
Remove bacon to paper towels.
Add onion and garlic to drippings.
Cook and stir 3 minutes.
Add beans, broth, water, Pace picante sauce, salt and oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
When ready to serve, ladle into soup bowls.
Top with sour cream and sprinkle with reserved bacon.
Serve with additional Pace picante sauce.
This is a hot spicy food.
Bill recommends Rolaids as an after dinner mint.

title: party mix
directions: Mix oil, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and A.1. sauce in a jar; shake well.
Mix Crispix, pretzels and nuts in a baking pan. Pour oil mixture over cereal mixture.
Bake for 2 hours at 250°, turning every 15 minutes.

title: holiday pudding cake
directions: Cook pudding according to directions on package in a 3-quart pot.
When it reaches a boil, take off the stove and
mix in the cake mix, using a large spoon.
Pour into ungreased spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool and frost with vanilla frosting.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.

title: quik brownies
directions: Mix above ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until batter curls away from sides of pan, approximately 45 minutes.
Cover with tinfoil when removed from oven.

title: peanut candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Pour into greased pan and let cool.
Then break into pieces.

title: toll house cookie pie
directions: Blend together oleo, sugar, egg and vanilla; add flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix well; blend in chocolate chips and nuts. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until lightly browned.
Edges will be set and soft in the middle.

title: dora's french dressing
directions: Beat well with electric mixer.
Keeps well and does not separate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash and slice squash and onions.
Cook squash until tender in just enough water to cover it.
Drain well.
Saute onions in small amount of butter.
Combine squash and onions (including sauteed butter) and mash.
Add salt and pepper.
Add soup and half the bread crumbs and mix well.
Butter 2-quart casserole dish and pour ingredients into dish.
Top with remaining bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: creamy crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl, except crabmeat.
Mix well.
Gently stir in crabmeat.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve with chips.

title: california fruit salad
directions: In a medium bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, honey, lime juice and lime peel.
Cover.
Chill.

title: "gran's" tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add slowly to batter. Refrigerate until cold.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place on cookie sheets.
Bake until lightly browned at 350°.

title: crock-pot pasta
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and tomatoes; simmer for a short while.
Cook shells and drain. Layer in crock-pot as follows: sauce, shells, sauce, cheese, repeat until all used, ending with cheese. Cook until hot and cheese is melted.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag and shake. Take 3 large cans of Hungry Jack biscuits and cut into fourths. Take half of biscuits and shake in plastic bag mixture. Put these in tube pan. Melt butter, add brown sugar and boil for one minute. Add 1/2 cup pecans. Pour half over biscuits in pan. Shake remaining biscuits in bag of sugar, put in the tube pan and pour remaining syrup over all. Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and mold into a loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Use 9 x 9-inch pan.
Place in pan in this order:
melted butter, graham crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips and pecans, then pour over everything the Eagle Brand milk.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.
Do not mix.
Ingredients are to be layered in pan.

title: ranch quick dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Great on salads or a vegetable dip or chip dip.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Make a well in the flour and pour in vegetable oil.
Add pumpkin and cold water. Blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour batter into two well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Put in ovenproof buttered casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: old fashioned hermits
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, egg and molasses.
Stir in flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Shape in long rolls on a lightly floured surface.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Press down lightly. Sprinkle with sugar (optional).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Cut diagonally into bars.
Cool on rack.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: microwave mexican chicken
directions: Layer 1/2 of all ingredients twice.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave on High 15 minutes.
Turn halfway through cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and sift together.
Set aside. Melt oleo and pour over cheese.
Add cheese to dry ingredients and cut in until it resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle water into this mixture.
Stir until all is moistened and shape into a ball.
Roll into 1/8-inch thickness on floured surface.
Cut into 3 to 3 1/2-inch strips.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Pour into greased mini muffin pans, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic salt.
Pour off fat.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in cheeses.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Serve warm on crackers or taco chips.

title: hot punch
directions: Put juices and water in the bottom of a coffee pot.
Put spices in basket.
Boil 10 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 cups.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Separate crusts and cut each into four squares. Place 1 apple half onto each square of pastry. Gather crust around apple to cover, pinching edges to seal. Place dumplings in a 13x9 inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and heat to a boil. Pour over dumplings. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until dimplings are golden brown. Serve warm with ice cream, if desired.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup in a 3-quart saucepan over moderate heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies.
Press into a buttered (greased) 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let harden.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in a double boiler; stir to blend.
Spread over top of cereal mixture.
Chill until top is firm.
Cut into squares.

title: any color punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add juices and cold water. Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serves about 30 people.

title: fresh kosher style dill pickles
directions: Make a brine of the vinegar, water and salt.
Boil.
Put dill, 1 clove garlic, 1/2 tablespoon mustard seed and 1 pod hot pepper in the bottom of each jar.
Add cucumbers.
Pour hot brine over them.
Seal.
Place in a deep pot of boiling water.
Leave in for 5 minutes.
Remove immediately.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with dried beef.
Wrap bacon around chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hi-ho cake
directions: Beat egg whites and add sugar until stiff.
Mix crackers, pecans and baking powder.
Add to egg whites.
Fold together. Pour into round cake pan that has been greased.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt margarine; cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well. Combine all dry ingredients and stir into egg mixture.
Rip 2 pieces of waxed paper, approximately 2 feet each and stack sheets together.
Pour batter on waxed paper, roll up lengthwise and refrigerate until very firm.

title: irish stew
directions: Flour meat and brown in a small amount of hot fat.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is almost tender. Stir frequently. Add carrots, parsnips, onions and potatoes. Cook about 20 minutes or until done.
Add peas and parsley. Cook about 5 minutes and serve hot.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 minutes or until firm in center.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Combine flour and powdered sugar.
Add margarine, mixing well. Pat dough out in a 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Combine cream cheese, condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Mix well and spread on cooled crust. Chill thoroughly.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in large saucepan; add water, mixing until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until thickened (about 5 minutes), stirring constantly.
Add strawberries; stir in food coloring.
Cool completely.
Spread strawberries and mixture over cream cheese layer and chill.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: grandma's portuguese dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make thin hamburger patties.
Layer bottom of pan.
Layer carrots (quartered), potatoes (quartered), 1/2 can green beans, 1/2 can corn, 1/2 bell pepper, 1/2 onion, salt and pepper.
Repeat again.
Pour can of tomato juice.
If you have any meat left over, make patties and cover top of vegetables. Cover pan.
Cook approximately 2 1/2 hours.

title: philly tortilly rolls
directions: Mix enough picante sauce in cream cheese to spread evenly over tortillas.
Add rest of ingredients.
Roll tortillas and wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice into small pinwheels and serve.

title: crayfish fettucine
directions: Saute onions.
Add crayfish and parsley.
Cook approximately 15 minutes.
In another pot simmer flour and cream until thickened.
Chop cheese and mix.
Add cheese mixture to crayfish. Boil noodles as directed. Mix all together and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil. Add carrots, celery and spices. When vegetables are tender, add green peppers.
Cook until done. Combine all other ingredients and heat together gently either in kettle or moderate oven, covered.
Serve topped with grated cheese.

title: jello cake
directions: Combine powdered sugar and lemon juice. Set aside.
Mix cake mix, Jell-O, apricot nectar and oil.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla and lemon juice. Bake in tube pan for 55 minutes at 325°.
When cake is done, lightly pour sugar/lemon juice mixture over cake, right from the oven.
Let cool in pan.

title: pistachio-pesto torta(20 servings)
directions: Create the following layers:
Combine cream cheese and Gorgonzola.
Combine green onion and pistachios.
Chop softened sun-dried tomatoes. Make pesto by combining basil, oil, garlic, Parmesan and nuts in food processor or blender.
Line a straight-sided bowl; mold with plastic wrap.
Add in layers as follows:
tomatoes, 1/3 cream cheese mix, pesto, 1/3 cream cheese mix, pistachios, 1/3 cream cheese mix.
Cover with wrap and chill at least 1 hour before unmolding.
Invert on platter.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Melt 1 stick butter with two cups graham cracker crumbs.

title: praline squares(cookies)
directions: Beat eggs with brown sugar; add oleo and beat well.
Add flour gradually.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 8 x 10-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan (greased or ungreased).
Top dough with pecans.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.
Check for doneness.
Looks like brownies.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 2 dozen squares.

title: strawberry fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: frothy lime-pear jello mold
directions: Dissolve lime jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and orange juice.
Arrange pears in lightly oiled ring mold or rectangular Pyrex dish; cover with lime gelatin.
Chill until almost set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo; add croutons.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Add 1 cup of croutons to mixture of broccoli, carrot, onion, cream of chicken soup and sour cream; stir.
Top with 1 cup croutons. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: southern chocolate-mint snaps
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Remove from heat.
Cream shortening.
Gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add melted chocolate, eggs, corn syrup, water and flavorings.
Mix well.

title: pasta primavera with roasted red peppers
directions: Roast 2 red peppers, either under broiler or above a burner flame, turning until all sides are charred.
Remove from heat and place in paper bag or damp towel.
Allow to cool.

title: cathy's creamy mince pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Fold whipping cream into mincemeat and spread into pastry lined pie pan.
Combine brown sugar and flour. Sprinkle over mincemeat.
Arrange pecan halves on top of mixture. Cover with top crust which has about ten 1-inch slits cut in it. Seal well by folding top crust under bottom crust and flute.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: cranberry-orange relish(microwave)
directions: Place whole cranberries in an oblong 7 x 11-inch baking dish; stir in sugar.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook 12 minutes, stirring and mashing every 4 minutes.
Put oranges through food processor.
Add to cooked cranberries.
Place nuts in small bowl; dot with butter.
Heat 3 minutes, stirring once.
Mix nuts into cooked cranberries; stir well.
Refrigerate, covered.
Serve with meat or poultry.
Keeps for weeks.
Makes 2 pints.
Can be frozen in small containers and used for gifts at holidays.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil the chicken (save 2 cups broth).
Debone chicken and spread in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle dressing mix over chicken.
Mix the 2 cups broth, butter and soup together in saucepan.
Heat until butter melts.
Pour over chicken and stuffing.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Separate eggs (save whites for meringue).
Mix all ingredients together except margarine and vanilla.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from stove.
Add margarine and vanilla and let cool 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Add your meringue and brown.
Cool and serve.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine celery, green pepper, onion, oil and garlic.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring 2 times.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp and rice.
Stir to blend and break apart tomatoes. Microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes or until flavors are blended, stirring once.
Stir in shrimp.
Microwave at power level 7 for 7 to 9 minutes or until shrimp are firm and opaque, stirring every 2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Power Levels: High and 7. Approximate Cooking Time:
21 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: easy dessert
directions: Spray a 9-inch square pan with cooking spray.
Pour pie filling into pan.
Pour pineapple and juice into pan and mix lightly with the pie filling.
Pour cake mix evenly across top and cut into pie filling, using a spoon. Dot with pats of oleo or butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until lightly brown.

title: finger icing
directions: Put first 4
ingredients in pan and heat until you can no longer stand to stir with finger.
Remove from heat and beat until stiff and fluffy.
Beat in salt, flavoring and color, if desired.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Put cube of margarine in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Set in oven to melt margarine.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and salt in bowl. Stir in 1 cup milk with dry ingredients.
Pour half of mixture in pan of melted margarine.
Add peaches evenly over mixture.
Pour rest of mixture over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add corn, sugar and egg.
Add milk to make a good drop batter.
Fry in deep fat. Makes 1 dozen.

title: perfect chocolate cake
directions: Mix together cocoa and boiling water and let cool.
Sift together cake flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Set aside. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and cocoa mixture alternately.
Pour into three 9-inch greased and floured cake pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: mary's strawberry pie
directions: Boil together until thick.
When thick, remove from heat and add strawberry Jell-O.
Cool.
Line baked pie crust with whole fresh strawberries and drip cooked mixture over berries.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate steamed pudding
directions: Grease the pudding mold and pour in.

title: cream cheese tassies
directions: Beat cream cheese and 1 egg at a time.
Add sugar and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Have 2 tassie pans with tassie paper cups in them.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in each and fill with cheese mixture to top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Decorate with Cool Whip and 1/2 of cherry.
Let cool before decorating.
Makes 64.

title: bread sticks
directions: Trim bread.
Cut each slice in 4 strips.
Melt butter and dip sticks of bread.
Roll in poppy seed and cheese.
Place 1/2 inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 250°, turning once.

title: pilgrim potatoes (baked)
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into uniform chunks. Boil until tender. Mash potatoes (using electric mixer); blend in spices and butter, then cream cheese, then sour cream. Whip until smooth and creamy. Put in square baking pan. Grate cheese and sprinkle on top of potatoes. Bake at 350° until cheese melts and starts to brown, approximately 15 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix all these ingredients together and pour half of mixture in a long pan or dish and refrigerate until jellied.
Then spread 1 pint of sour cream over top.
Pour rest of mixture on top and refrigerate.

title: cinderella crisps
directions: Trim bread crusts, cut in strips, lengthwise, about 3 strips to one slice.
Using 2 forks, roll strips in milk coating on all sides, then roll in coconut.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool one minute; remove from cookie sheet.

title: chicken french
directions: In shallow bowl, beat eggs and cheese; set aside.
Coat chicken in flour and dip in egg mixture.
Heat oil in skillet. Brown chicken slowly on both sides and remove to paper towel. Drain any oil from pan.
To the pan, add margarine, bouillon cube and water.
Add chicken pieces, sprinkle with lemon juice and pour on the sherry.
Simmer 10 minutes or until tender, turning chicken occasionally.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Heat all ingredients over low heat until melted.
Serve with taco chips.

title: easy chocolate-oatmeal drop cookies(another home ec favorite!)
directions: Bring sugar, evaporated milk, cocoa and margarine to a boil in a saucepan.
Boil for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Do not stir.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto a greased pan or waxed paper.
Let cool and enjoy! (Easy no-bake recipe.)

title: tiny reubens
directions: Spread party rye with hot mustard, next pastrami, corned beef or ham, then sauerkraut.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Sprinkle with parsley or paprika.
Broil until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Simmer all the above until zucchini is tender.
Put in blender until smooth.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Can be served hot or cold.
Freezes well.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: gator sauce piquant
directions: Alligator may be marinated in wine for 1 hour before adding to sauce.
Saute onions in oil until dark golden brown, stirring often.
Bell pepper and celery are then added and sauteed until tender.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings; simmer for 10 minutes, then add mushrooms and drained alligator meat. Cover and cook for 40 minutes.
Add shallots and parsley.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: sticky buns
directions: Let thawed bread dough rise until doubled in size.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in saucepan and stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and chopped nuts.
Remove from heat as soon as melted and blended; pour into 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Punch down dough and roll into 13 x 17-inch rectangle.
Spread with melted butter.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over dough.
Roll rectangle, beginning at long side, and pinch ends to seal.
Cut into 1-inch slices and arrange in pan over butter topping mixture.
Cover and allow to rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from pan immediately and turn upside down onto platter. Yields 16 buns.

title: spanish rice with beef
directions: Brown meat with spices and onion.
Add everything else but rice and bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Mix oil, sugar and egg and beat well.
Stir in molasses.
Sift together dry ingredients and add.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup sour cream.
Spread into baked and cooled pie shell and refrigerate.

title: cream celery soup
directions: Cook celery and onion in 1 cup water until tender.
Melt butter and spread in flour, then add milk.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Add cooked celery with liquid.
Heat gently, then season to taste with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley. Makes 4 cups.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Layer spareribs in a slow cooker.
In a mixing bowl, combine tomato soup, vinegar, brown sugar, soy sauce, celery seed, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Pour over spareribs.
Cover pot and heat at medium setting for 6 to 8 hours.
Skim fat from juices before serving.
Keep warm at low setting.

title: wet bottom velvet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and oleo like pie dough and take 4 handfuls out; set aside.
In another bowl, mix molasses, water and baking soda.
Then add to first mixture.
Pour in pans, sprinkle with a handful of crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: In a bowl, puree avocados; add Tabasco sauce, lemon juice, parsley and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in tomatoes and cucumbers.
Place in serving bowl and add sour cream on top or in separate bowl on the side.
Serve as dip with tortilla chips or raw vegetables.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins 15 minutes in 2 cups water.
Let cool.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Combine flour, spices and baking soda.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Add raisins and water last.
Bake at 350°.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine soften cream cheese and marshmallow cream. Mix until blended. Serve with fruit or cookies. Makes 2 cups.

title: brown edge wafers
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Mix flour and salt together.
Combine all ingredients.
Drop a teaspoonful at a time on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse and soak lentils overnight.
Combine all ingredients. Add water to cover lentils.
Bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Cut sausage in bite-size pieces and add to soup (optional).

title: holiday little prune cakes
directions: Mix prunes, sugar and eggs, then beat in oil, then buttermilk. Add soda and salt, add flour slowly.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour mini muffin cups, fill 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool. Frost with cream cheese frosting and decorate as desired.
Makes about six dozen.

title: chile relleno puff
directions: Arrange half of the chiles in bottom of well-greased 9-inch baking dish.
Top with half of the tortilla strips and half of the cheese.
Arrange tomato slices on top of cheese layer.
Repeat layers with remaining chiles, tortillas and cheese.
Beat together the eggs, milk, cumin, garlic, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over tortilla mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika or mild chili powder.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 40 minutes until puffy and center is set.
Allow to stand about 10 minutes before cutting into squares.
Serves 6 to 8.
Serves 10 to 12 if using a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: wassail
directions: In crock-pot or on stove, heat, then lower temperature.
Serve hot.
Happy holidays.

title: frozen blueberry creme
directions: Reserve a few blueberries for garnish.
In a blender, puree remaining berries with 1 cup evaporated skim milk, sugar substitute, and sugar.
In a saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over cold water.
Dissolve gelatin over low flame.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice.
Stir gelatin mixture into blueberry mixture.
Whip remaining 1/2 cup evaporated milk until thick but not stiff.
Fold into blueberry mixture.
Pour into 2-quart bowl.
Freeze for several hours, stirring occasionally, until mushy.
Spoon into dessert dishes while still soft.
Garnish with blueberries.
Serves 8.

title: heavenly butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix milk, pudding and ice cream until smooth.
Spread into pan. Refrigerate 45 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip, remaining crumbs and Butterfingers.

title: oriental tuna salad
directions: Drain juice
from pineapple into small bowl.

Mix 1 tablespoon juice with mayonnaise, soy sauce and garlic salt; cover and chill. Just before serving, line medium size bowl with lettuce leaves; break remainder into bite-size pieces and place in bottom of bowl. Arrange tuna, green pepper strips, pineapple chunks, water chestnuts, green onions and rice noodles in ribbons over lettuce. Spoon soy dressing over top.
Toss lightly to mix.
Serves 4.

title: turtle bars
directions: Melt caramels and milk in microwave.
Combine cake mix with water, butter and eggs.
Pour 1/2 of batter into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until gooey cake puffs up.
Pour melted caramels evenly over cake.
Sprinkle on chips and nuts. Pour remaining batter on top and bake 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: swiss liver
directions: Cover pieces of liver with flour and seasoning.
In large frypan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onions, tomatoes and basil.
Cover with lid.
Reduce heat to low and cook 1 hour.

title: cheddar burgers
directions: Combine first six ingredients and mix well.
Form into 5 patties.
Grill or broil to desired amount of doneness.
Serve in buns. Top with additional Heinz 57 sauce if desired.
Yields 5 servings.

title: gingerbread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar; stir in ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add egg.
Beat until well blended. Stir in molasses and buttermilk.
Sift together flour and soda. Combine with batter, beating just until flour is incorporated. Pour into a greased 10-inch iron skillet.
Bake in a 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: easy mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until bubbly.
Freezes well.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mash avocados in a bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper. In a separate bowl, combine the next 3 ingredients.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour and dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until smooth.
Place in greased and floured loaf pans or small coffee cans filled 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: becky's peanut butter fudge
directions: Spray 13x9 inch pan with non-stick spray.
Microwave margarine in four quart bowl on HI for one minute or until melted. Add sugar and milk.
Mix well.
Microwave on HI six minutes or until mixture begins to boil, stirring after three minutes.
Mix well, be sure to scrape sides.
Microwave on HI seven minutes, stirring after three minutes.
Gradually stir in peanut butter chips until melted.
Add marshmallow cream and mix well.
Pour into pan.
Cool at room temperature, cut into squares.

title: cranberry ice
directions: Boil cranberries in water and strain. Add sugar and corn syrup and bring to a boil. Dissolve Jell-O in hot mixture and cool. Put in lemon and orange juice and freeze. Remove from tray and beat. Then freeze again. Serve in sherbet glasses.

title: easy pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Very crisp.
Keeps well for about 2 weeks.

title: grits souffle
directions: Combine grits, water, salt and 1 tablespoon butter in a medium saucepan. Cook over medium-high heat 5 minutes.

Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Add remaining butter, milk, egg yolks, pepper, paprika and cheese. Stir until cheese melts. Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form. Gently fold into grits mixture.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart souffle dish. Sprinkle heavily with additional paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve immediately. Serves 8.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 2 skillets.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In a double boiler, melt butter and chocolate.
Slowly add sugar.
Add salt.
Add milk.
Stir well until blended. Refrigerate.
To reheat: Spoon needed amount in coffee cup and heat in microwave for 1 minute.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Brown meat; add mushrooms, garlic, onion, celery and Italian seasoning.
Stir together over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add Ragu and stir well.
Grease 9 x 13 pan with olive oil.
Layer half the eggplant on bottom.
Add half the meat mixture and top with 6 slices provolone.
Layer remaining eggplant, meat and provolone. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread mozzarella cheese on top. Cover with foil (spray foil with PAM) and cook 30-45 minutes at 325-350 degrees.
Take foil off last 10 minutes to brown cheese.

title: pluckets
directions: Pile balls loosely in ungreased angel food cake pan.
Let rise 30 minutes.
When baked, turn the pan upside down immediately. Serve warm.

title: salmon kedgeree
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Combine ingredients in top of a double boiler and heat over hot water.
Serves 6.

title: lemon cottage cake
directions: Melt butter in glass pie pan on High for 45 seconds in microwave.
Stir in crumbs and sugar.
Mix until all ingredients are moistened in pie plate.
Press up sides and bottom. Microwave 1 1/2 minutes, rotating 1/2 turn after 1 minute.
Cool. Beat cottage cheese until smooth.
Blend in pudding powder and water.
Pour in crust and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together and then add dressing.

title: dandelion dressing
directions: Saute bacon until browned.
Add water to bacon and drippings. Combine egg, flour, vinegar and sugar; mix well.
Add to bacon and water, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and freshly ground pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until dressing is thickened. Pour over greens just before serving and toss quickly.
Serves 4.

title: whipped frosting
directions: Beat oleo, Crisco and sugar for 4 minutes.
Add scalded milk (cooled).
Beat well.
Add in egg; beat until creamy.
Add any flavoring.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream Ricotta, cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, sour cream and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Pour into spring-form pan.
Place spring-form pan in a large pan. Add one inch of water to pan and put in oven.

title: dolly o'neill's spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach well.
Mix all the other ingredients with the spinach.
Add oil, salt and pepper.
Take a teaspoon of mixture and roll into balls.
Dredge in flour to coat.
After all the balls are made, drop into large pot of boiling water.
Watch closely.
When they pop to the top, they are done.
Remove with a slotted spoon.
Can be served alone or with pasta sauce.

title: doritos delight
directions: Brown meat and onion; add salt, pepper, soup, milk and chicken.
Spread Doritos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture on top of chips and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chewy butterscotch bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add sugar.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add vanilla and sifted flour and nuts.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into small bars.

title: banana punch slush
directions: Boil water and syrup for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add pineapple, lemons, orange juice and bananas.
Mix, freeze overnight.
Take out and mash with a potato masher.
Pour 3 liters ginger ale over it.
Serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water; drain.
Rinse in cold water; drain again.
Mix onion, salt and French dressing; mix well. Combine mustard and salad dressing; add pickles, carrot and pepper.
Toss lightly and chill until ready to serve.
Add boiled eggs, if desired.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt butter.
Pour in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour on greased cookie sheet in thin layers.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: hot rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a covered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Stir once during cooking.

title: hot soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Dissolve yeast, sugar and salt in warm water.
Stir in flour.
Place on floured board; knead for 10 minutes.
Pinch off small strips of dough.
Roll into ropes between palms.
Shape like pretzels.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy color cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugars.
Beat in vanilla, water and egg. Sift remaining dry ingredients together and add to the sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in M&M's candies.
Drop from teaspoon to ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 3 dozen 2 1/2 inch cookies.

title: lemon lush dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and pecans.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Combine sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Mix and spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding and cold milk.
Spread on cheese mixture.
Spread rest of Cool Whip on top.
Chill.

title: country vanilla ice cream
directions: Add sugar gradually to beaten eggs; continue to beat until mixture is very stiff.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into gallon container and freeze as directed on ice cream maker.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix together and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: crazy crackers("yummy to the tummy.")
directions: Place butter and brown sugar in small pan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Place saltines in a cookie pan with sides.
Pour butter mixture over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. Immediately sprinkle with chips and nuts.

title: saxo spinach dip
directions: Melt Velveeta and cream cheese together.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
It's best to thaw the spinach beforehand.
May be served hot or cold.

title: vickie's beef and mushroom spread
directions: Place softened cream cheese in a large mixing bowl.
Add chopped olives, onions, mushrooms and dried beef; mix thoroughly. (May be rolled into logs or balls.)
Roll in chopped pecans until covered.
Chill.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: holiday christmas log
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Shape into 10-inch rolls.
Brush with additional heated corn syrup and roll in additional chopped nuts. Wrap tightly and store in refrigerator 3 to 4 days to blend flavor.
To serve, cut into slices.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Add baking soda, warm water, vanilla and flour.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: butterscotch pie filling
directions: Brown butter; add milk and egg yolks.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt; add to milk mixture.
Cook until thickened; cool slightly.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff; beat in granulated sugar.
Pile meringue lightly on pie. Bake in a 400° oven until meringue is lightly browned.

title: pound cake
directions: Place sugar, Crisco, butter and flavoring in mixer bowl and store, covered, at room temperature overnight.
Have eggs in carton at room temperature overnight.

Beat sugar, Crisco, butter, vanilla and lemon flavoring at medium speed of mixer until fluffy and sugar is no longer grainy. Sift together flour and baking powder. Add flour mixture to sugar mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition.

title: mandel bread
directions: In a medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add melted butter and vanilla.
Combine flour and baking powder in a bowl.
Add to the egg mixture.
Add almonds.
Stir until well blended.

title: 20-minute cacciatore
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook chicken with garlic and black pepper 10 minutes or until chicken is lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Add spaghetti sauce and green pepper.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Serve over macaroni.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheesy broccoli
directions: Place broccoli in a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Add cheese and spoon soup over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Mix stuffing mix with melted oleo.
Press 1/2 of the mix into casserole dish for the crust.
Spread the squash on crust.
Mix sour cream, onion and cream of chicken soup.
Spread over the squash.
Add the rest of the stuffing mix.
Spread with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Arrange bread pieces, bacon and cheese in greased casserole. Pour melted butter over this.
Beat eggs, salt, mustard and milk. Pour over casserole.
Let stand 3 hours or overnight, covered in the refrigerator.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°, uncovered.
May pour into a 9 x 13-dish.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together; shape into ball.
Leave a little of the beef for sprinkling on top.

title: ranch style biscuits
directions: Mix and knead in large bowl.
Refrigerate.
Place biscuits in greased pan.
Let rise 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: janet's fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add well beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk to mixture. Add vanilla flavoring.
Mix thoroughly.

Add fruit, raisins and nuts and mix by spoon or hand until thoroughly mixed, then drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake in preheated oven at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes (cookies will be light brown).
Be careful not to overcook.
Test cookie after approximately 15 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut the elephant into bite-sized pieces.
Add the vegetables and enough water to cover.
Cook over an open pit, in a large pot, for 2 weeks.
Stir the stew everyday.
This will serve about 3,800 people.
If more people are expected, the 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only in an emergency!
Most people don't like hare in their stew!!!!

title: butterscotch crunchies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in microwave or can use pan on low flame. Stir in noodles and nuts until blended and coated. Spoon mixture by teaspoon on waxed paper. Cool completely.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press into an 8 1/2 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Beat the last 3 ingredients.
Pour over the first mixture. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato kisses
directions: Remove	all
lumps from potatoes; beat in melted butter and sugar.
Beat
until blended.
Add cocoa or melted, cooled chocolate;	add
vanilla, salt and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed	paper.	Place
in refrigerator for a short time to harden.
Place
in	a
tightly covered container.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine beef and onions in skillet; cook until meat is lightly brown.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole or a 9 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place sliced cheese over hamburger mixture.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in order given in a 12 x 9-inch dish.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread evenly over top of salad.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Whisk together eggs and 1/4 cup of sugar until well blended. Whisk together remaining 3/4 cup sugar and flour in a 2-quart saucepan, then whisk in water and vinegar. Bring to the boil, whisking until sugar is dissolved. Add to egg mixture in a slow stream, whisking constantly with wooden spoon until filling coats back of spoon and registers 175° on an instant-read thermometer, 12 to 15 minutes. Pour hot filling into pie shell and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool completely on rack and dust with cinnamon. Makes 8 servings.

title: apple macaroon
directions: Pare and slice apples in casserole until half full.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Sift together 1 cup sugar, flour and salt.
Make a hollow in this and drop in 2 eggs.
Stir until well mixed.
Spread mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: taco casserole
directions: Break taco shells and use them to line a 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Combine meat, beans, sauce, onions and chili powder. Cover shells.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Before serving, top with shredded lettuce and diced tomatoes.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion and saute together until tender. Add mushroom soup, water, cheese and broccoli; blend together. Add Minute rice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 or 12.

title: chocolate cherry cordial drops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cookie mix, egg and water in large bowl.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Stir in cherries and coconut.
Shape dough into 36 balls.
Roll in nuts.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 11 to 12 minutes or until cookies are set and lightly browned.
Cool 1 minute on baking sheet.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add syrup, salt, flavoring.
Beat well.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add pecans and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake slowly in oven at about 300° for about 1 hour.

title: applesauce raspberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries.
Stir until thawed.
Stir in applesauce.
Chill until set.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand several hours or overnight.
Gets better with age.
Can be kept in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cut carrots crosswise and cook until tender.
Melt half of the margarine and cheese and stir together.
Put carrots in casserole dish and cover with cheese mixture.
Crumble crackers and mix with the other half stick of margarine.
Sprinkle on carrots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pumpkin nut bread
directions: Mix flour, spice, soda, salt and baking powder.
Beat sugar, oil and eggs in a large bowl.
Beat in pumpkin and 1/3 cup water. Stir in flour mixture, then chocolate chips and nuts.
Scrape into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack and cool completely. Freezes well.

title: curry chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve on lettuce with fruit salad and hot rolls.

title: a cook's delight
directions: Fry diced bacon ends until brown and drain.
Peel potatoes and dice; cook with at least 1 quart string beans until almost tender. Brown flour in a bit of bacon grease.
Add bacon pieces and brown flour to the cooking beans and potatoes until it is the desired thickness for soup.

title: carameled popcorn
directions: In saucepan, melt oleo, brown sugar and syrup.
After it comes to a boil, lower heat and boil for 6 minutes; remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon soda and 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Stir until foams good, then pour over popped corn and mix well.
If you want popcorn balls stop now and make into balls.
If you want carameled corn, place on 2 cookie sheets and put into 200°
oven for 1 hour.

title: nachos casserole
directions: Spread refried beans in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cook ground meat with taco mix and onion and layer over beans in baking dish.
Pour jar of picante sauce over ground meat.
Place sliced olives (and green chilies, if using them) over picante sauce and top with cheeses.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes until cheese is bubbly. To serve, top with sour cream and chopped tomatoes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dresdener stollen
directions: Combine raisins, currants, candied citrus peel, angelica and cherries in a bowl.
Pour the rum over them, tossing the fruit about to coat the pieces evenly.
Soak for at least 1 hour.
Pour the lukewarm water into a small bowl; sprinkle it with the yeast and a pinch of sugar.
Let the mixture stand for 2 or 3 minutes, then stir to dissolve the yeast completely.
Set the bowl in a warm, draft-free place (such as a turned off oven) for about 5 minutes, or until the mixture is almost double in volume.

title: pizza meat loaf pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine beef, milk, egg, bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons tomato paste.
Mix with hands until well blended.
Lightly grease a 9-inch glass pie plate.
Spread mixture on bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread remaining tomato paste over surface of meat mixture.
Arrange onions and mushrooms over top.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and oregano.
Place on bottom rack of preheated 375° oven. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until crusty.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: baked cheesy green beans
directions: Cook beans according to package directions; drain.
Combine soup and cheese spread.
Toss beans with soup mixture; place in 6 cup casserole.
Top with onions and bacon.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Yield:
About 6 servings.

title: creamed spinach
directions: In medium skillet, cook bacon until almost crisp.
Add onion to bacon and cook until tender, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add flour and spices; blend well.
Gradually stir in milk, starting with 1 1/2 cups.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Add spinach and mix thoroughly.
If too thick, add additional milk.

title: lumpia shanghai filipino egg rolls
directions: Mix ground pork, shrimp, 1 egg, green onion, carrot, sesame oil, salt and pepper in mixing bowl.
Roll in lumpia wrappers about 1/2 inch thick.
Seal with egg whites.
Fry in oil on medium heat on all sides until brown.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: french bread crunch
directions: Mix butter and dressing.
Cut loaf in half.
Spread mixture on bottom and on top half.
Place buttered sides up in broiler. Brown slowly until done and crunchy.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Simmer chicken on a rack with 6 cups boiling water for 2 to 4 hours, with the celery, carrot, onion and rosemary and salt.
Cool chicken; bone and skin meat, cut into big cubes.
Strain the broth and refrigerate.
Next day, skim 3 tablespoons fat from broth into double boiler.
Mix in flour.
Add 1 1/2 cups broth.
Cook until thickened and slowly stir in the egg yolks, mixed with the cream. Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Saute the mushrooms in the additional chicken fat for about 4 minutes.
Add the mushrooms to the sauce in the double boiler.
Add the cubed meat (about 3 to 4 cups) and reheat in the sauce.
Cook the spaghetti in rest of the chicken broth and water.
Drain.
Put the cooked spaghetti around the edge of a deep casserole dish and fill the center with the sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and dot with butter.
Brown quickly under the broiler.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together; add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into pie crust and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: maryland's sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend or whip until light and fluffy.
Place in souffle dish or other glass dish.
Bake around 350° to 400° until golden brown.

title: chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Clean chicken and cut in strips.
Place chicken pieces in a large skillet sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and saute until lightly browned.
While chicken is cooking, place butter in a saucepan and melt over medium heat, then add flour, salt and pepper and stir until blended.
Add chicken broth and stir with a whisk; add cooking sherry and continue to stir.
Add evaporated milk and continue to whisk until mixture thickens.
Turn burner off.
Cook broccoli in microwave for about 5 minutes.
Place broccoli in casserole dish and pour half of white sauce over it.
Layer chicken on top.
Add Parmesan cheese to rest of sauce.
Pour over top of chicken.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and bake for 30 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Servings of rice to suit yourself, add Italian dressing to taste.
Add enough seasoned salt that the color of rice is almost orange.
Add all vegetables to your own taste.
(All vegetables are optional.)
Except you do need some onions, tomatoes and lettuce.
Add small pieces of lettuce just before serving.
The rest should be added 30 minutes to 1 hour before serving.

title: sue's meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small balls. Roll balls in flour and fry them until they are lightly browned.
(I use a medium boiler and deep fry them, it's easier.)
Add them to the sauce.
These are the best meat balls and sauce.
Put over spaghetti or fix meat ball hoagies and top with Mozzarella cheese. Fix ahead and freeze.
(I freeze them in quart containers.)

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown onion, bacon and hamburger.
Drain.
Add the rest.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: debbie's banana breeze
directions: Bake pie shell.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add Eagle Brand milk; blend.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir until thickened.
Slice 2 bananas and line baked pie shell.
Turn filling into crust and top with 2 more sliced bananas and enough Cool Whip to cover bananas.
Refrigerate.

title: new orleans french quarter doughnuts
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Combine flour, sugar and salt and set aside.
Heat water to boiling.
Add flour mixture all at once, stirring to form a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition until mixture is smooth and glossy.
Stir in peel.
Drop dough by teaspoon in 3 to 4 inches hot fat (about 5 minutes) until golden brown.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: elegant strawberry punch
directions: In a 6-quart container, mix together all ingredients, except ginger ale.
Cover loosely and freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer at least 4 hours before ready for use.
Partially thaw and break into chunks.
Add ginger ale and stir slowly until slushy. (Mix in a large punch bowl when ready to serve.)
Makes about 28 (6 ounce) servings.

title: lemon pie(lo-cal)
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Kool-Aid together.
Pour into pie crust. Chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook meat and onion until onion is soft.
Add tomatoes and bay leaves.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until vegetables are done.
Add remaining ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove bay leaves.

title: sour cream banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine all ingredients except powdered sugar and beat for 3 minutes.
Bake in prepared (greased and floured) Bundt pan for 60 minutes.
Cool for 1 hour.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat in a large pot.
Add all the vegetables and V-8 juice.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Put in large bowl.
Chop peppers, slice onions and add to beans.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over and stir in.

title: corn bread
directions: 1. Mix dry ingredients. Combine egg and buttermilk and stir into dry ingredients.
2. Pour batter into a hot well greased pan.
3. Bake in a 450° oven 20-25 minutes.

title: mexican dinner
directions: Layer all ingredients in Pyrex container. Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve with tossed salad.

title: peach pie cake
directions: Put in long glass Pyrex dish in order as listed.
Let peaches set for 10 minutes with tapioca over them.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix.

title: bremer kukenragot (german)(chicken ragout)
directions: Sprinkle chicken parts with salt. Melt margarine or butter and brown chicken pieces on all sides.
Pour in bouillon mixture. Cover and simmer over moderate heat for about 15 minutes or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken to warm platter.
Pour off bouillon, saving 1 1/2 cups (save rest of bouillon for other recipes or soups).
In saucepan, stir small amount of bouillon into flour.
Gradually add remaining bouillon, cooking over medium heat, stirring constantly. Add frozen shrimp. Cover and simmer until shrimp are thawed.
Stir in peas and mushrooms, sour cream and asparagus.
Heat gently but do not allow to boil.
If desired, add the lemon juices. Serve over chicken pieces with mashed potatoes and a green salad.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In a large pot, brown sirloin and drain. Add all ingredients except for noodles.
Simmer on low heat until green beans are done, approximately 20 minutes to 1/2 hour.
Cook noodles separately. Rinse and drain. Add to soup just before serving.

title: chocolate chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine flour and baking soda; set aside.
In bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract until creamy.
Beat in egg.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in morsels and nuts.
Drop by level tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheets for 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mash the potatoes until the lumps are gone and place the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased dish.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in hot 425° oven for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini italian milano
directions: Note:
Zucchini should be cubed and steamed to desired tenderness (approximately 3 cups).

title: congealed salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in water.
Add lime jello; set to soft congeal.
Fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip and remainder of ingredients.
Congeal.

title: molasses oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix in eggs, vanilla and molasses.
Stir together the dry ingredients.
Add to the mixture. Stir in the oatmeal, raisins, chocolate chips and walnuts. Grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen cookies.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Peel onions and slice into thin rings.
Saute in butter for 15 minutes.
Put layer of onions, crackers and cheese in dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
