To dress up, top with French fried onion rings.
Allow to heat awhile.

title: luscious lemon bread
directions: Cream 2/3 cup of sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and stir. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add lemon rind and nuts. Bake at 350° in a well greased loaf pan for 1 hour.
While bread is baking, combine remaining 1/3 cup of sugar and juice of saved lemon.
As soon as you take the bread out of the oven, poke holes in it with a toothpick and drizzle the lemon sugar mixture over it.
Let stand in the pan until cooled.

title: easy easy caramel pie
directions: Put unopened can of condensed milk in saucepan and boil slowly in water for 3 hours.
While can is warm, punch small hole in top and let out steam.
Open can and put in graham cracker crust. Chill, cover with whipped cream and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; save broth.
Debone
chicken.
Cook celery and onion in oleo until tender.
Add cheese and mushroom soup.
Cook noodles in broth and drain.
Add chicken and noodles to mixture, then add olives.
Heat at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: frozen apple-snow salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add water to pineapple syrup to make 1/2 cup.
Combine syrup mixture, beaten eggs, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Chill.
Fold in apple, pineapple, celery and the whipping cream.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine with shortening. Add sugar and beat until smooth. Add egg yolks, one at a time, as you beat the creamed mixture.

title: french quarter bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
In Dutch oven, combine beans and enough water to cover.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Cover; let stand 1 hour.
Or, soak beans overnight in water.
Drain.
Add 6 cups fresh water and ham hock. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well; bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, soda and salt together.
Cut in oleo. Mix like pie crust.
Grind raisins and stir in.
Combine egg, pineapple, juice and Sweet*10.
Add to first mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle coconut on each cookie and press with back of fork so they are level.
Bake at 300° or 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut and cook the zucchini and onion in water until tender. Drain well.
Add the chicken soup and sour cream and mix.

title: veal scaloppine
directions: Dip veal slices in beaten egg and then in bread crumbs, coating veal well.
Heat olive oil in large frying pan and brown veal on both sides.
Remove.
Put on platter and fry onions and garlic in same oil.
Add a little more oil, if needed, then add green pepper and stir until onions are limp and peppers look cooked.
Add mushrooms, juice and tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and water.
Stir to mix well.
Put cover on and cook for 5 minutes.
Place veal into pan and cook until veal is tender. Serves 4 people.

title: shrimp ala creole
directions: In oil, add onions, pepper, celery and garlic.
Cook until wilted.
Add tomato, seasonings and shrimp.
Cover; cook on low for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: barbecue sauce for crab
directions: Cook crab as usual. Mix all ingredients and heat.
Put clean, cracked crab pieces in sauce.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil pepperoni 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add butter and a generous amount of Parmesan cheese to spaghetti.
Cook onions and ground beef together; drain. Add tomato sauce and seasonings to meat; simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add drained mushrooms to meat sauce after it simmers. Layer in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish in this order:
spaghetti, grated Mozzarella cheese, pepperoni, meat sauce and sliced Mozzarella cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into individual serving dishes or large serving bowl.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers. Preparation time:
5 minutes.
Total time:
35 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cold oven butternut cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Fold in flavoring, cherries and nuts.
Grease a tube pan (large).
Start in cold oven and do not open oven door until done. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 35 minutes.
Remove from pan soon after taking from oven and cool on wire rack (inverted).

title: garlic herb bread
directions: Cut bread into 1 1/2-inch thick slices.
Blend together butter, garlic and oregano.
Spread on bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil until top is light brown and bubbly, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Night before:
Grease a large casserole.
Cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Cut cream cheese into 1 inch cubes.
Put half of bread into casserole, top with cream cheese and cover with rest of bread.

title: egg custard rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Add butter, salt and dry custard mix.
Stir until dissolved.
Add flour gradually. Mix well.
Knead on lightly floured surface 12 to 15 times.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, make into desirable shapes. Let rise double in bulk.
Bake at 375° until done, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes good cinnamon or sweet rolls!

title: graham cracker pudding cake
directions: Make your favorite chocolate and vanilla puddings.
Line a 13 x 9-inch cake pan with whole graham crackers.
Spread with half the chocolate pudding.
Layer again with graham crackers.
Spread with half the vanilla pudding.
Refrigerate until chilled.
When ready to serve, top with freshly whipped cream.

title: sprouts with sour cream
directions: Add 1-inch of water and Brussels sprouts to a saucepan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: fried mush
directions: Bring 5 cups water to boil.
In bowl add 1 1/2 cups water with cornmeal and salt.
Add mixture gradually to boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cook 3 minutes.
Reduce heat to low and cook 15 minutes longer.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Cool to room temperature.
Cover and refrigerate.
Loosen mush along sides with knife.
Place on inverted plate and turn over.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Fry over medium heat in large skillet.
Brown each side, turning once.
Transfer to platter.
Keep warm in 300° oven.
Serve with butter and corn syrup.

title: hello dolly's
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9-inch cake pan.
Lay ingredients in pan, beginning with vanilla wafers and adding the pecans on top.
Pour the can of condensed milk over the entire mess.
Place in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Pour off grease.
Slice potatoes in casserole.
Add vegetables.
Put meat on top.
Pour in soup mixed with water.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Take cover off last 15 minutes.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cut up and brown bacon in pan.
Add flour and butter; mix. When butter is melted, add vinegar, water, sugar, salt, pepper and onion.
Pour over cut up warm potatoes and serve.

title: confetti scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt butter. Saute onions until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper, pimento and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Pour into a shallow casserole dish.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lightweight chicken
directions: Place chicken skin side down in a nonstick skillet.
Place the vegetables on the chicken and sprinkle with Mrs. Dash.
Cook on very low heat for 35 minutes until chicken is brown on one side and moisture has been drawn out of vegetables (use no oil).
Turn chicken over and cook over low heat for another 35 minutes.
Do not cover skillet during cooking.
Mushrooms may be added during the last 20 minutes of cooking.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix; make small balls.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil water, brown sugar and sugar for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add instant coffee.
Let cool (cold).
Add vodka.
Put vanilla bean (split) in large bottle with liquid mixture.
Let set for 2 weeks.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef brisket
directions: Marinate brisket in 1/2 cup sherry for 2 hours, turning every 1/2 hour.
Mix 1/4 cup sherry with dry onion soup mix.
Put on top of brisket.
Wrap in heavy foil with sauce and bake 4 1/2 hours at 300°.
Cool and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, slice meat and pour juice over meat.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve.

title: bean and rice chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain fat.
Add green pepper and chili seasoning mix.
Cook and stir until pepper is tender.
Stir in water, beans and tomato sauce.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chiles and corn; bring to boil.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat. Fluff with fork and sprinkle with cheese.

title: frozen punch
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar and hot water; then add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Add enough water to fill a gallon plastic jug almost full.
Freeze.
Let thaw 4 hours before serving.
Add 1 quart ginger ale.

title: mexican fricassee
directions: In saucepan, cook green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve on cooked rice.
If desired, garnish with Cheddar cheese.

title: spicy peanut chicken wings
directions: In a shallow baking pan lined with foil, season the chicken with salt and pepper and bake in the middle of a preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes or until they begin to turn brown and become crisp.

While the wings are baking, in a small saucepan, stir together the peanut butter, the soy sauce, the honey, the garlic and the red pepper flakes and cook the mixture over low heat stirring, until it is smooth.
Brush the chicken wings generously with the sauce and bake them 10 to 15 minutes more or until the sauce is set.
Sprinkle the chicken wings immediately with the chopped peanuts and cilantro and let them cool slightly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frikadeller(danish meat patties)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients well except margarine. Melt about 1/4 cup margarine in large skillet.
Using a large salad spoon, dip into the margarine, then into the meat and form a ball. Put on skillet.

title: bean casserole
directions: Drain all the cans of beans well.
Brown bacon and drain off fat.
Mix brown sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in 350° oven for 3/4 of an hour.

title: sparkling cooler
directions: Make tea in advance adding the boiling water to the tea and mint flakes.
Allow to cool, then chill.
Just before serving, strain tea into a tall, chilled pitcher.
Add the sodas.
Stir to mix and garnish with fresh mint sprigs and lemon slices.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Crumble bread and soak in milk.
Mix other ingredients into bread/milk mixture.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
(Can be frozen.)

title: meat filled shells
directions: Put hamburger in skillet.
Add Italian seasoning, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Brown hamburger and set aside.
In same pan, add a little oil and cook onions, green pepper and celery.
Mix with hamburger and add enough spaghetti sauce so it will stick together good.
Pour remaining sauce in bottom of pan.
Stuff shells with mixture and arrange in pan.
Pour most of second jar of sauce over the stuffed shells.
Top with cheese.
Cook 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water; drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients, except 1/2 stuffing and 1 stick oleo; mix well.
Line shallow dish with remaining stuffing that has been mixed with 1 stick oleo.
Reserve a little for topping.
Fill with squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: one pan rice pudding
directions: Pour rice slowly into boiling water.
Cover and cook 7 minutes.
Add the milk and butter.
Stir a little and bring to a boil, cover and turn to low and cook for 1 hour.
Meanwhile, beat eggs, add sugar, raisins and vanilla.
Pour mixture into rice. Stirring slowly until rice starts to thicken and bubbles.
Serve hot or cold with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar sprinkled on top.

title: double cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar, flour and buttermilk.
Beat two minutes. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat two more minutes.
Add soda, salt, baking powder, vanilla and extract.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan or two bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour. Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove from pan and cool completely.

title: gloria's peach cobbler
directions: Combine peaches and margarine.
Heat together until margarine melts.
Mix sugar, flour, milk and baking powder.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: macaroni and shrimp salad
directions: Boil macaroni in lightly salted water; drain, and cool.
Mix mayonnaise, salt, and mustard.
Combine
all ingredients and mix well with mayonnaise mixture.
Chill and serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix egg yolks (save whites for meringue), sugar, coconut and flour.
Add salt and milk.
Mix well.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and put into browned pie shell.
Beat egg whites.
When stiff, beat in 6 tablespoons of sugar.
Top pie, sealing around the edges and sprinkle with coconut.
Brown in 350° oven.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix Ro-Tel tomatoes with chilies and 8 ounces sour cream together. In each tortilla, put chicken and sour cream mixture. Roll and place in pan. Mix together soup and 8 ounces sour cream. Pour over stuffed tortillas. Cover with cheeses. Bake at 350° until cheeses melt and tortillas are hot. Serve with picante sauce.

title: jalapeno pepper pie
directions: Line pie pan with peppers. Spread cheese on top of peppers. Beat eggs, salt and pepper. Pour on top of cheese. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple cherry crunch(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chopped apples in medium bowl. Drain cherries; save juice.
Add cherries to apples; set aside. In small saucepan combine cherry juice, cornstarch, 1/2 cup apple juice concentrate and 1/4 cup fructose.
Stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add almond and pour over fruit.
Pour fruit mixture into 2-quart casserole which has been sprayed with vegetable spray.

title: fruity shake
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender on high until ice is chopped fine and mixture is blended.
Serve immediately in tall, chilled glasses.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 10.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: grandma's applesauce meatballs
directions: Beat egg; add milk and croutons.

Soak until soft. Beat crouton mixture until soft and fluffy. Add remaining ingredients (except water and soup!). Shape into small balls (golf ball size) and place in 9 x 13 pan or cup cake pan. Add water to mushroom soup. Mix together and pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add water to make 1 c. liquid. Reserve pineapple. Blend juice and cornstarch and stir on medium heat until thick and clear. Add remaining ingredients, including pineapple. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, garlic and parsley in olive oil until soft.
Add meat and brown.
Blend in juices and spices.
Cook slowly for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Spoon off excess oil. If sauce becomes too thick, add small amounts of water.

title: bachelor buttons
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and egg in a mixing bowl with a mixer.
Add other ingredients and hand mix.
Roll in small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Mash down with fingers.
Bake at 370° for 8 minutes.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook the noodles in a large amount of boiling, salted water and drain.
In Dutch oven, combine the ground beef, chopped onion, green pepper, celery and garlic.
Cook until meat is lightly browned.
Stir in tomatoes, sauce, mushrooms,, cheese, thyme, basil, salt and pepper.
Heat and stir until cheese melts.
Spread noodles in two 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dishes.
Pour tomato mixture over; stir into noodles.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake 45 minutes.
Uncover; stir lightly.
Bake 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with 8 ounces of sharp process American cheese.
Bake 5 minutes.
Makes 25 (about 1-cup) servings.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix dry pudding and Cool Whip.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir well and refrigerate.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots.
Cook until tender; drain off water. Mix soup, salad oil, vinegar, sugar, dry mustard and chopped pepper.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat; add carrots and onions. Put in covered dish and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain cooked squash.
In a bowl mix soup, carrots, onion and sour cream.
In a 2-quart casserole, combine the soup mixture with the squash.
Melt 1/2 block or stick of butter.
Mix with 1/2 package of herb seasoning.
Place the herb seasoning mixture on top.
Cook 45 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together well. Spoon into 9 x 13. Bake for 20 minutes at 350° (until bubbly). Remove from oven. Top with cornflakes or cracker crumbs mixed with 1/4 of the butter. Return to oven until browned (5 to 10 minutes).

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and cornstarch in pan. Add milk and stir while cooking. Add beaten egg yolks and mix well. Cook until fairly thickened. Stir in oleo and vanilla. Pour into cooled baked pie shell. Add whipped cream to top before serving.

title: greek salad
directions: Thinly slice onion, pepper and cucumber into mixing bowl.
You can cut rings in half or smaller, if desired.
Add dressing generously.
Cover bowl and marinate overnight.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Oven toast pecans in butter and salt.
Mix cream cheese, milk, beef, green pepper, onion and pepper.
Fold in sour cream and half the nuts.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle remaining nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Wash, de-seed and dry chilies.
Wrap split chilies around 1/4-inch sticks of Jack cheese.
Lay in bottom of glass casserole dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
In a large bowl, beat the eggs, milk, flour and jalapeno peppers.
Pour mixture over the cheese and chilies.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Saute onion.
Mix beef, crumbs, salt, pepper and eggs.
Add onion and 1/2 of tomato sauce.
Form into a loaf and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Combine flour and sugar; cut in butter until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Pour milk into deep mixer bowl.
Add Dream Whip and instant pudding.
Beat 4 to 6 minutes.
Place whole graham crackers in a 7 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in half of pudding mix.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Pour over it the remaining pudding.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Cover with chocolate frosting.

title: famous pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add salt, well beaten eggs, syrup, and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in a raw pie shell for one hour at 300 degrees.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cherries.
Heat to almost boiling.
Remove from heat, and dissolve Jell-O in juice.
Pour mixture over pineapple, cut up cherries and whipped cream cheese. Add pecans, stir in Coca-Cola slowly.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Put in tight lidded container.
Use 2 tablespoons and 1 teaspoon per cup of hot water.

title: chicken crescent squares
directions: Cook chicken; cool and cube. Blend all ingredients (except rolls). Separate crescent rolls. Spoon chicken mixture onto crescent rolls. Seal rolls around mixture and put into baking pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: game pie
directions: Clean the birds thoroughly and split into halves; cover with water and heat to boiling.
Skim top and add salt, pepper, parsley, onion, cloves and salt pork.
Simmer until tender, keeping birds covered with water.
When done, thicken the liquid with browned flour and let the gravy come to boiling.
Add fat, remove from fire and cool.
Line sides of greased baking sheet with pastry.
Fill dish with alternate layers of bird and potatoes.
Pour gravy.
Cover with crust and bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix cereals, pretzel sticks and peanuts in a large roaster. Heat margarine to melt but not brown.
Add Worcestershire sauce and seasonings to margarine.
Pour over cereal combo; mix well. Toast in a 300 oven for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Stir every 10 minutes to get seasoned margarine evenly distributed through the mix.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Combine all ingredients except last two.
Turn into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine 1/4 cup cracker crumbs with 1 tablespoon butter.
Sprinkle over vegetables and bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Note:
Use pineapple juice with water for liquid in cake.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla and beat.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Stir in walnuts and apples. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: oven crisped halibut
directions: Remove skin, wash and cut off feet.
Soak an hour in salt water.
Beat an egg lightly.
Salt and pepper legs.
Dip in meal or crumbs, then in egg.
Dip again in meal.
Fry in deep fat.
Be sure to drain off all grease when finished.

title: matt and jason's favorite tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix with soups.
Put in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Top with Tater Tots, then with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mother's meat loaf
directions: Mix using 1/2 onion and 1/2 can soup.
Put in baking dish. Sprinkle with other 1/2 of the onion on top.
Pour over the remaining soup and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta fagioli
directions: Cover bottom of saucepan with oil.
Brown chopped garlic in oil.
Add cannellini beans, pepper, salt and tomato sauce.
Add elbow macaroni.
Cook about 1/2 hour.
Serves 4.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and onion and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cabbage and onion.
Mix all together.
Will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Add 1 cup sugar to egg whites.
Beat until stiff; set aside.
Add 1 cup sugar to egg yolks.
Beat until light and fluffy; set aside.
In large bowl, add dry ingredients, then add egg yolks, oil and sweet potatoes.
Mix well.
It's a thick batter.
Add the stiffened egg whites and mix well.
Bake in well-greased large square pan for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: deviled chicken
directions: Blend sugar, mustard, water, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce together.
Use to moisten chicken.
Then shake chicken pieces in bag with seasoned coating mix, one at a time, as directed on package.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes or until chicken is well browned and tender. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ginger beets and pineapple
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, powdered ginger, salt and pepper. Add pineapple tidbits with syrup.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly until bubbly and slightly thickened.
Add beets.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: campfire cheese spread
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: chess cake squares
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg; press on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs and pour over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool and cut into squares, 1 to 1 1/2-inches.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let simmer for 35 minutes.
Serve on warm buns.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until creamy.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda and mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecan pieces.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls (about 2 measuring tablespoons) of dough 3 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Don't overbake.
Cool on baking sheet for 2 minutes, then remove to foil or countertop. Yield:
about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: butterscotch pudding
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix xxxx sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip; spread on crust.
Beat pudding and milk until thick.
Spread on cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour beef
directions: Shake beef in a bag with flour.
Put into casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Add onions.
Cover and bake at 375° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Great served with rice!

title: "miss willies'" fried apple pies
directions: Cook apples and cinnamon according to directions on package. Cool (I cook my apples the day before); sweeten to taste.

title: baked apple and carrot casserole
directions: Place half the apples in a greased 2-quart baking dish and cover with half the carrots.
Mix brown sugar, flour and salt; sprinkle half the mixture over the carrots.
Repeat layers and pour orange juice over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: tomato casserole
directions: Place ingredients in
casserole
in
order shown above. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apricot ambrosia
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in apricot nectar gradually.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture is thickened and clear, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Drain apricots, reserve 12 halves for decoration and chop remaining apricots.
Stir chopped apricots into cooked mixture. Add pecans.
Tear cake into bite-sized pieces.
Add to cooked mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top each serving with Cool Whip.
Place reserved apricot half, cut side down, on each. Yields 12 servings.

title: holiday chocolate
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounces of almond bark in bowl on High for 2 minutes.
Stir, continue microwaving 1 to 2 minutes, or until smooth when stirred.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts. Pour into greased 11 x 14-inch dish.
Top with cherries; sprinkle with coconut.

title: melt in your mouth pumpkin bread
directions: Mix oil and eggs.
Add pumpkin.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Divide the mixture into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour, or until taste test is done.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar and water.
Boil until all moisture is boiled out. (Peanuts will be coated with sugar.)
Stir continuously.
Pour onto cookie sheet and bake at 300° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes or until all nuts are well toasted. Stir occasionally.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Add flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and pie filling.
Stir.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans until golden brown at 325°.

title: caribbean pork 'n' rice
directions: Cook slice pork tenderloin in a little oil in a large skillet. Add onion and chopped carrot and cook until pork is no longer pink. Stir in pineapple chunks, water, barbecue sauce, ginger, green pepper and rice.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.

title: nacho layer dip
directions: Layer each ingredient on a plate in the order given.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: vegetable medley casserole
directions: Melt margarine and crumble Ritz crackers.
Mix together and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together and place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with margarine mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and oil; beat until fluffy.
Stir in pumpkin.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into pumpkin mixture. Add water, raisins and nuts; blend well.
Spoon batter into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all together and when ready to serve, put on French dressing.
May add a diced tomato, a can of kidney beans or chopped fresh onion and sliced black olives.

title: tuna loonies
directions: Mix together.
Fills at least 15 hamburger buns.
Wrap in foil and put in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Can be frozen.
If so, bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: dessert dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl. Cut in butter.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix until moistened. Set aside.

title: cole slaw for sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stir regularly during refrigeration overnight.
Excellent on sandwiches or alone.

title: strawberry delight dessert
directions: Stir together all the ingredients until moistened.
Layer this in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place in refrigerator.

title: beefy jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, milk, eggs, salt, soda, corn and jalapeno peppers in a bowl.
Mix and set aside.
Saute meat, onion and bell pepper until lightly browned.
Drain fat.
Thoroughly grease a 10 1/2-inch iron skillet.
Pour half of cornmeal batter into skillet.
Sprinkle evenly the meat mixture, then cheese. Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: banana sherbet
directions: Combine water and sugar and cook until sugar is dissolved. Add orange juice, lemon juice and mashed bananas.
Cool and freeze. When soft mush in consistency, remove from freezer and fold in beaten egg white (Not too stiffly beaten)
Continue freezing until firm enough to serve. Makes 2 qt.
Keep covered when stored.

title: peach jam
directions: Peel,
core and chop peaches.
Stir lemon juice into peaches. Measure sugar, make sure cups are level across the top.
Pour peaches and Sure-jell in large boiler.
Add butter to keep from foaming.
Bring mixture to a full rolling boil.
Stir constantly. Add sugar to peaches.
Bring back to a full rolling boil.
Cook for 2 minutes;
remove from heat.
Skim off foam.
Fill jars and seal.
When cold,
check to see if sealed by pressing finger in middle of lid.
If lid springs up it is not sealed, eat this jar first.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put
cranberries
through coarsest cutter of meat chopper. Let stand overnight with marshmallows and sugar.
Before serving add celery, nuts and whipping cream.

title: for goodness sakes salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve the gelatins in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Stir in the milk, pineapple with juice, mayonnaise, cottage cheese, nuts and horseradish sauce; mix well.
Chill until partially set.
Pour into an oiled 8-cup mold.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.
Unmold.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: prize winning pound cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Place cake in oven and then turn temperature to 300 degrees.
DO NOT PREHEAT OVEN. Bake for 1 hour-turn cake around and bake 20 minutes more.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat eggs until light. Beat into mixture until creamy.
Mix in apples and nuts.
Add flour mixed with baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Stir lightly into apple mixture.
Turn into a buttered 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: ham and cheese balls
directions: Tear each biscuit into thirds.
Wrap this around a cube of ham and cheese.
Shape into ball.
Seal well.
Stir onion in melted butter.
Roll each ball in onion butter, then in potato chip crumbs.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Yields 30 appetizers.

title: baked chicken
directions: Bone 4 good-sized whole chicken breasts (or buy them already boned).
Marinate in beaten egg for several hours.
Sprinkle with onion salt.
Roll in Italian flavored bread crumbs.
Saute in vegetable oil.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle again with onion salt and oregano (optional).
Slice fresh mushrooms and spread on chicken.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over chicken.
Mix bouillon cube in 1 cup hot water and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at
350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break cake up into small pieces, put in the bottom of a bowl. Mix pudding and 2-1/2 c. cold milk.
Pour over cake.
Cut strawberries up and mix into glaze.
Spread over cake and pudding. Spread Cool Whip over strawberry mix.

title: turkey broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
In a large bowl, combine turkey, broccoli, cheese and pasta; mix well.
In another bowl, blend soup, sour cream and mayonnaise thoroughly. Pour over turkey mixture.
Toss lightly to coat.
Pour into prepared casserole and bake for 30 minutes.

title: italian meat fingers
directions: Mix
beef
and
pork in a large bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Chop
parsley and garlic together.
Add to meat. Squeeze water from bread.
Add bread, cheese and beaten eggs. Work mixture
with
your
hands
to
combine all ingredients. Shape into fingers about 1/2 to 3/4 inch in diameter and about 1 1/2 inches
long.
Heat
olive oil and fry over medium heat until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: homemade salsa
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together tomatoes, chili peppers, green onion, green pepper, lemon juice, parsley, garlic and pepper.
Place about 1 cup of the tomato mixture and tomato sauce in a blender container or food processor bowl.
Cover and blend or process just until pureed.
Stir into remaining tomato mixture.
Cover and chill for several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: cherry surprises
directions: Cream sugar, vanilla, butter, nuts and flour.
Wrap a walnut size portion of dough around cherries.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Chill 15 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix eggs, meal, milk and corn together. Add pepper, onion and cheese.
Add oil last and mix well.
Bake in two 8-inch skillets at 450° for about 30 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes before serving.

title: hot chicken and cheese heroes
directions: Combine chicken, celery, almonds, onion, lemon juice, salt, pepper and mayonnaise in bowl; mix well. Cut thin slice from top of rolls. Hollow out centers. Fill with chicken mixture. Arrange in baking dish. Chill, covered in refrigerator until cooking time. Sprinkle rolls with cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Serves 4.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Filling:
In a medium saucepan combine cornstarch, sugar and lemon juice; mix well.
Beat egg yolks.
Add to cornstarch mixture.
Add water.
Bring mixture just to boiling over medium heat and simmer gently for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and lemon rind to thickened mixture and stir until thoroughly blended.
Pour into baked pie shell. Prepare meringue.

title: summer salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix together mayonnaise and vinegar.
Then toss with vegetables and macaroni.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 8.

title: stromboli
directions: Let bread dough rise at room temperature 2 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Place dough on foil.
Flatten into large square.
Spread with spaghetti sauce, towards center.
Layer cheese, meat, cheese and meat over surface of dough, leaving edges uncovered.
Sprinkle with Italian seasoning.
Roll dough into a loaf, making sure meat and cheese are inside.
Secure loaf by squeezing ends together. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour or until loaf is golden brown.
Turn once for even baking.
Let cool 25 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish. Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and dot with 1/4 cup margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: In bowl, beat eggs; add sugar, flour, butter and salt.
Mix well, then add corn and milk.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until firm.

title: eggs a-la-russe
directions: Take the eggs and prepare them as for deviled eggs.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Spoon over eggs.
Place parsley leaf on each egg, then sprinkle with paprika.

title: funny putty
directions: Mix together.
If it is too sticky, add more starch.
Add paint for color.

title: spaghetti sauce for 80
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and green pepper in 1/2 pound butter until tender clear.
Add crumbled ground beef.
Cook until done and browned.
Drain well.
While beef is cooking, combine rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Add drained meat mixture. Simmer gently for 2 hours.
Quick cool in ice bath.
Refrigerate overnight.
Skim solidified fat from top before reheating.
Use tomato juice to thin if needed.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients.
To this mixture, add bananas and milk.
Pour into a well-greased bread pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 large loaf or 2 smaller loaves.
If using the smaller pans, watch time.
When tester comes out clean, bread is done.

title: cornbread skillet casserole
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in bowl; set aside.
Cook beef until browned; drain well and set aside.
Pour half of cornmeal mixture into greased 10-inch skillet.
Sprinkle evenly with beef. Top with cheese, onion and peppers.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Stir together frozen blueberries and pineapple.
Spread yellow cake mix on top.
Cut patties of butter and lay on top of cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: almond roca
directions: Melt butter over high heat.
Add sugar, stirring constantly (mixture will foam).
Continue cooking and stirring; add almonds. Continue to cook until mahogany colored (take it off the heat for a moment if it starts to smoke).
Stir while removing from heat and pour into jelly roll pan (cookie sheet with sides).
After 5 minutes, pour chips on candy and spread.
Sprinkle walnuts on top. Candy is done when chocolate is dull.
Cool completely and break into pieces.

title: amaretto bonbons (microwave)
directions: Combine chips, corn syrup and sugar.
Add coffee to boiling water to dissolve.
Add to other mixture.
Heat in microwave until chocolate is melted.
Remove.
Stir in Amaretto, cookie crumbs and nuts.
Chill until you can roll it into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut.
Keep tightly covered in a container in the refrigerator. Makes about 40 balls.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix together in heavy pan the sugar, syrup and water. Cook until it spins a thread and turns a light brown when dropped into cold water.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce; mix until smooth.
Add pineapple and pecans.
Mix cream cheese and enough pineapple juice to spread easily.
Congeal half of jello mixture.
When firm, spread cream cheese over this.
Add remaining half of jello mixture and congeal.

title: fluffy meat loaf
directions: Mix altogether and shape into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: granola
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Mix remaining ingredients (except raisins) in a large bowl.
Pour liquid mixture over dry mixture and mix thoroughly, leaving only a few lumps. Spread on 2 greased baking sheets or large roasting pan (to prevent spills).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until dry but not browned. Stir frequently and watch closely.
Can also be baked at lower temperature until dried.
When dried, add raisins and mix.
Cool thoroughly.
Store in jars or plastic bag.
Yields 9 cups.

title: white cake
directions: Light-as-a feather, this cake can be served as is or with fresh or frozen fruit, raspberries are especially delicious.

title: cocktail onion crisps
directions: In a large bowl, measure first 5 ingredients.
Cut with pastry blender 1/4 cup butter into flour mixture.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Knead until blended.
Preheat oven to 370°.
Divide dough into 4 equal pieces.
Roll each piece (one at a time) into a 12 x 12-inch square (as thin as possible).
In small pan, melt remaining margarine.
Brush dough with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with dried onion flakes.
Roll into dough with rolling pin.
Cut dough into 2 1/2 or 3-inch squares.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet, approximately 8 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Make burger into meatballs.
In skillet, put in all other ingredients.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Add meat; cover.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve on rice.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef in saucepan. Drain. Add chilli mix, pintos and tomato sauce to ground beef. Bring to a boil. Let simmer about 20 minutes or until thick. Take softened cream cheese. Spread in bottom of baking dish. Then spread beef chilli mixture on top of cream cheese. Next, sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese on top is melted.

title: chilled fruit soup
directions: Soak dried fruits and tapioca in water 2 to 3 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients, except cherries, and add to first mixture. Bring to boil and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Add cherries.
Remove cinnamon stick and cloves.
Chill.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat.
Mix with other ingredients. Pour into 2 1/2-quart dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix granulated sugar, 1/2 c. flour and cinnamon together and set aside. In a huge bowl or 8-quart pot, mix the apples and flour/sugar/cinnamon mixture till the apples are fairly well coated, then pour them into a 9 x 13 cake pan.

title: hydrox cookies mixture
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk in double boiler; cool.
Mix with whipped cream.
Roll cookies rather fine.
Put layer in bottom of dish.
Spread with mixture.
Top with cookies.

title: brown sugar cake
directions: Spread in
pan and top with crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: harvard pot
directions: Melt margarine in medium-size skillet.
Add onions and green pepper; cook until limp.
Remove and set aside.

title: cranberry pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Break up and stir in cranberry sauce.
Add pineapple, orange juice and lemon juice. Chill until partially set.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into an 11 x 7-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares; serve each on a lettuce leaf with a dollop of mayonnaise.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: cheesy gougere puffs
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Spray a nonstick muffin tin with oil. Bring water, butter, cayenne and herbs to a boil over high heat. Remove from heat and add flour, beating vigorously with large wooden spoon until dough forms a ball and pulls away from sides of pan.
Return to medium heat, still beating with a spoon, 1 minute to dry dough.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: In a large pan, combine Jell-O with boiling water until gelatin
is dissolved.
Fold in strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half of mixture in dish and refrigerate until firm.
Spread the top with sour cream.
Gently spoon the remainder of strawberry mixture and refrigerate until firm.

title: blackberry brandy slush
directions: Boil first two ingredients; set to cool.
Steep tea bags in 2 cups hot water, then cool.
Mix all mixtures together.
Freeze overnight.
Mix 1/2 slush with 7-Up.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Crumble noodles and add to water; stir in seasoning packets.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Drain noodles. Combine noodles and butter, stirring until butter is melted.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring gently to coat.
Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Yields 4 servings.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: sweet and sour pork roast
directions: Remove roast from fridge and allow meat to come to room temperature.
Carefully insert meat thermometer, so that bulb doesn't touch a bone or is embedded in fat.
Place on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Put in preheated oven (325°).

title: sourdough bread
directions: Mix real well together, then pour into Starter.
Let stand out of refrigerator 8 to 10 hours, with lid on very loosely, until bubbly.
Take 1 cup Starter to make bread and return rest to the refrigerator 3 to 5 days and feed again.
(Always keep lid on Starter loose.)

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream softened butter with 1/2 c. 10x sugar, vanilla and salt until fluffy.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Chill 30 minutes or until firm enough to handle.
Shape in 1 inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on cookie sheets and bake at 375°, 12-15 minutes until golden.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco, sugar and eggs for 1 minute at high speed. Add 1 cup flour, beating 1 minute.
Add other 2 cups flour alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°, then turn heat up to 350° for 10 to 20 minutes, or until cake is golden brown.

title: western ranch dinner
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Dip cut up chicken in Pet milk; roll in mixture of Bisquick, salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt shortening in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven.
Add chicken and bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Make biscuit dough.
Move chicken to one end and cover with peach halves.
Spoon biscuit dough in other end.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil, cocoa, margarine and water. Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and soda in a large mixing bowl. Add boiling mixture and mix well. Add eggs, then buttermilk and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured 1 x 1-inch sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Five minutes before removing cake from oven, bring cocoa, milk and margarine to a boil, then beat in powdered sugar and vanilla. Pour and spread evenly on hot cake. When cool, cut into squares. Excellent for freezing. Remove squares from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: sweet vidalia onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a medium bowl, mix together crushed crackers and 1/3 cup melted butter. Press mixture firmly into a 9-inch pie pan and set aside.

title: tomato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour, sugar plus all dry seasonings.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in tomato juice. Bring to boil.
Stir constantly and boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Stir hot mixture into milk.
Heat and enjoy.

title: grilled chicken with chives
directions: Brush chicken pieces with melted butter and add about 1 teaspoon herbs per piece.
Add salt and pepper. Wrap tightly with foil.
Grill, turning once.
Total cooking time should be about 40 minutes.
Perfect for busy or hot summer days.
(Chives, parsley, tarragon and thyme are good with this.)

title: dump cake
directions: Stir together pie filling and pineapple; put in buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Dump dry cake mix over mixture.
Add nuts and spread evenly.
Cut butter in wedges and arrange over the top of nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash squash and cut into chunks.
Cook in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Add onion, margarine, cheese, sugar, eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 40 minutes.
Freezes well.
May prepare ahead.

title: caramel puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, chips and caramels in a medium saucepan.
(While these are melting, place cereal in a large bowl.) Add peanut butter to caramel mix; stir until well mixed.
Remove from stove; pour over cereal.
Stir to coat well.
Spread cereal on 1 to 2 sheets of waxed paper to cool (about 1 hour).
Return to bowl with a lid; top with powdered sugar.
Replace lid and shake!

title: green chile cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer until well blended, using enough cream for a dipping consistency.
Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: paula's six week bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Will keep up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Fill tins as needed.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: In a saucepan, brown ground beef. Drain. Add chili, cheese and green chilies. Heat over medium-low, stirring frequently until cheese melts. Serve warm with chips.
Yields 12 servings.

title: surprise yellow cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on cake mix. Pour in a 13 X 9 pan. While cake is still hot poke hole in it with a toothpick and pour Eagle Brand Milk over it. Let cool then pour crushed pineapple, partially drained, over cake. Sprinkle coconut and pecans over the top of cake. Spread cool whip on top.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers to a powder. Chop cherries, leaving 5 or 6 for decoration. Melt marshmallows in milk. Mix all ingredients, a little at a time, into hot marshmallows. When mixture becomes cool, you can begin mixing with your hands. You will need to add cherry juice as you mix to keep ingredients moist. Place a drinking glass on cake plate and pat the cake mixture around glass until you "make a cake" around it. Set in the refrigerator until firm. Remove glass.

title: bac*os salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: johnny cake
directions: Bake 1/2 hour at 350° in a flat pan or loaf pan.

title: holiday layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut margarine into cake mix until it resembles coarse crumbs; pat into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Layer marshmallows, chips, coconut and nuts over crust. Pour sweetened condensed milk over mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Chill, if desired.

title: key lime cake
directions: For icing make another glaze to desired consistency.

title: mama's lil' pizzas
directions: Makes as many little pizzas as there are in the biscuit tube.

title: cuisinart banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use metal blade.
Put the flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and nuts in the work bowl and process for 10 seconds or until the nuts are coarsely chopped.
Remove the mixture and reserve it.

(Make several loaves in sequence by processing all the dry ingredients and nuts for each recipe first. You won't have to wash the work bowl between batches of batter for each loaf.) Process the bananas for 1 minute or until pureed. Add the
sugar and eggs and process the mixture for 1 minute.
Add the butter and process for 1 minute.
With the machine running, pour the buttermilk and vanilla through the feed tube.
Blend in the reserved nut mixture by turning the machine on and off 3 to 5 times or until the flour just disappears.
Do not overprocess the batter.
Pour the batter into a buttered and floured 7-cup loaf pan and bake for 1 hour or until the bread is brown and a cake tester inserted in the center comes out clean.
Turn the bread out on a wire rack and let it cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: hawaiian delite
directions: Mix pudding, pineapple and pineapple juice; beat with mixer for 2 minutes.
Add nuts and Cool Whip; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: susan's perfect sauce bearnaise
directions: Combine wine, vinegar, shallots, 1 tablespoon parsley, pepper and tarragon in saucepan.
Simmer until reduced by 1/3.
Cool and strain (about 2/3 cups liquid).
Beat egg yolks with salt in top of double boiler.
Place over simmering water and heat in strained wine mixture.
Mix thoroughly, then add cold butter.
Cut in 1-inch cubes, one at a time, stirring constantly.
As one cube melts away, add the next.
Cold butter keeps the sauce from curdling.
Watch carefully and, if necessary, lift top pan occasionally while stirring.
Stir until desired thickness is reached.
Remember, sauce will thicken as it cools.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining parsley.
Serve cold with hot steak, swordfish or salmon.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut flour, salt and lard together.
Add egg, water and vinegar. Makes two large 2 crust pies.

title: james' irish oatmeal scotchies
directions: Optional:
Use 1/2 butterscotch morsels and 1/2 chocolate morsels and 1/2 cup coconut (to make cookie chewy).

title: fran's minestrone soup
directions: Use a very large, deep pan (8-10 quarts).
Shred cabbage and carrots.
Chop onions and celery.
(If using a food processor, use the grater blade for all vegetables.)
Melt butter and add garlic and onions.
Cook slowly until onions are transparent.
Be careful not to let burn.
Add cabbage, carrots and celery.
Cover and cook for 25 minutes, stir frequently.
Add vegetable broth and 8-10 cups of water.
Add bouillon and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add beans (don't drain), pasta, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.

title: quick and easy biscuits
directions: Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 500° until done.
Makes 8.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and onions.
Put in heavy pan with butter or margarine, broth, salt and pepper.
Simmer until potatoes are soft.
Whisk until it becomes thick and potatoes show no lumps.
Add half and half, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Stir in the parsley or chives.
Reheat.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir in margarine.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Put on bottom of buttered 10-inch pie plate.
Brown beef, onions and peppers.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, sugar and spices.
Spread cottage cheese on spaghetti crust.
Put tomato mixture on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Put cheese on top and bake until melted.
Freezes well.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar real well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Add flavoring.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add flour alternating with sour cream. Pour mixture into a slightly greased tube pan.
Place on lowest rack in oven. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 35 minutes or until done.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill milk in freezer until ice cold.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool until partially set.
Then whip the partially set jello until it is light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and sugar; mix well.
Set aside.
In large bowl, beat chilled milk until stiff peaks form; fold in the jello mixture.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with vanilla wafer crumbs, reserving a few to sprinkle on top.
Pour lemon mixture into pan over crumb crust.
Sprinkle the reserved crumbs on top.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: top banana cake
directions: Mix butter, frosting mix and oats; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Beat eggs, sour cream, bananas and cake mix.
Pour 1/3 batter in pan and then crumb mixture; repeat.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.

title: aunt dora's baked macaroni
directions: Add
salt,
beaten egg yolks, cheese, baking powder and milk to	cooked	macaroni.
Then add onion and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: salt substitute
directions: Mix together.
Place in salt shaker and use in place of salt. Can be used on just about any vegetable or meat.

title: crepes
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Slowly add flour and sugar alternating with milk and water.
Then beat with blender or the electric mixer until smooth.
Beat in oil.
Chill for 1 hour.
Pour scant 1/4 cup of batter onto griddle.
Cook until top is set, underside is just brown.
Flip and cook other side.
Can be filled with fruit and sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Also filled with mixture of cinnamon and regular sugar.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with ice ring.

title: potato puff
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and potatoes.
Mix well until blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed chicken in a pot
directions: Break bread into pieces.
Brown butter, celery and onion in skillet over medium heat until celery and onion are done.
Pour water over celery and onion and bring to boil.
Put bread in large bowl; add seasonings and mix well.
Pour water mixture over bread and mix until bread is moist.
Stuff chicken and put in crock-pot on low.
Mix 2 cups water with 4 cubes of chicken bouillon.
Pour over chicken in crock-pot.
Let cook overnight, or 8 to 10 hours. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix together rhubarb and 1/2 cup sugar; set aside. Mix together remaining ingredients, then add rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until done.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.
Drain and keep warm.
Place margarine in large nonstick skillet; place over medium heat until hot.
Add broccoli, carrots, onions, garlic and basil; saute 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp and tender, stirring often.
Add mushrooms, salt, pepper and water.
Cook 2 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.
Gently toss pasta with vegetable mixture and cheese.
Yield:
9 servings. (About 146 calories per 3/4 cup serving.)

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: *Broccoli, cauliflower, celery, carrots, onions, pea pods, asparagus, green beans, bean sprouts, mushrooms and green onions.

title: congo squares
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and margarine.
Add flour, nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Add few drops of water.
Mix well.
Bake in a large greased pan at 325° for about 20 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: popped corn in the oven
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Pop the popcorn.
Put half the popped corn in each of 2 baking pans (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix the brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until it gets bubbles around the edge.
Cook for 5 minutes more, then take the pan off the heat, stir in the soda until it is foamy.
Pour half the sauce over the popped corn in each pan.
Stir it so the popped corn is covered all over.
Bake the caramel corn 1 hour, but stir it every 15 minutes.
Let the caramel corn cool.

title: turkey-potato pancakes
directions: Combine eggs, potato, turkey and onion.
Add flour, salt, pepper and sage; mix well.
Drop about 1/4 cup of batter for each pancake onto hot, greased griddle, spreading to about 4 inches in diameter.
Cook over medium-low heat for 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Serve with cranberry sauce, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hershey's 5 minute recipe fudgy brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda in mixing bowl. Blend in 1/3 cup oil. Add boiling water. Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup oil.
Add flour, vanilla and salt. Blend completely.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or into two 8 x 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
If using 2 pans, 30 to 32 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan caramels
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2 pan with foil; butter the foil with 1 tablespoon butter.
Sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips; set aside.
In heavy saucepan over medium heat, melt remaining butter. Add brown sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until a candy thermometer reads 248° (firm ball state).
Pour into prepared pan (do not scrape saucepan).
Cool completely before cutting.
Yield: about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Coat chicken pieces in flour.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken, brown well on all sides.
Drain oil from skillet.
Add remaining ingredients to skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken and juices run clear, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot cooked pasta.

title: danielson chili(the only title it's had)
directions: Brown
hamburger;
break
into small pieces. Add kidney beans, catsup and sugar.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over mashed potatoes. Good for potluck as meat side dish.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.

title: scrambled eggs creole
directions: Put in a skillet 2 tablespoons butter and 1 slice onion, diced.
Cook 5 minutes. Add tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add eggs (beaten slightly) and grated cheese.
Stir and cook until creamy.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and boil squash until soft.
Brown onion, pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Drain squash and mash with browned mixture.
Add 4 tablespoons margarine, 1/2 cup cheese, cracker crumbs and seasoned salt to taste.
Add beaten egg and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes in a 12 x 8 x 1-inch pan sprayed with nonstick spray.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels in baking dish.
Add 3 tablespoons of sugar, nuts and melted margarine.
Bake 7 minutes at 350°; let cool.

title: hollywood two tone cheese cake
directions: Crush zwieback fine, then put through a food mill.
Combine with sugar and batter.
Mix thoroughly.
Grease a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan with 1 teaspoon of shortening.
Cover sides and bottom with 1 cup of crumb mixture.
Pour rest of mixture in bottom of pan; press smooth, then chill.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, eggs and 3/4 teaspoon vanilla; beat until smooth. Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand for 10 minutes.
Increase oven temperature to 450°. Blend sour cream, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour over cake and bake for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool before removing the spring-form.
Cover with waxed paper and refrigerate for 12 hours or longer.

title: chicken romano
directions: Preheat oven to
425°.	Mix first 5 ingredients together. Pour milk into
shallow pan.
Dip chicken into milk, then roll in crumb mixture.
Place in ungreased pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix together filling ingredients (everything except tomato sauce) in a large bowl.
Use good sized pinch of mixture to each leaf.
Place ball of mixture in stem end of leaf.
Fold over sides, toward middle and roll whole packet up as you would an egg roll.
Place fold side down in a baking dish.
Cover with tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Add soup, mayonnaise and onion powder. Pour into a small casserole dish.
Top with cheese, stuffing mix and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: banana peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together except sunflower seeds.
Add seeds after everything is mixed well.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Don't overcook.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with juice of pineapple which has been boiled. When it begins to jell add other ingredients.
Mold in ring mold.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter, flour and confectioners sugar.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Separate roll dough into rectangles.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan, stretching to cover and sealing edges and perforations.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.

title: creamy waldorf salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, Cool Whip and sugar together with mixer.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Put in large, clear bowl.
Place red and green cherries around sides and on top of salad.

title: hard rock candy
directions: Place syrup in a saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir to hard boil stage.
(Mixture caramelizes slightly as it cooks.)
Remove from heat.
Stir nuts, butter and coconut in.
Pour into a well-greased cookie sheet. Chill for 2 hours.
To eat, break off pieces.

title: frosted chewies
directions: Place sugar and corn syrup in medium size saucepan; stir to combine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture just boils good.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and mix well.
Add cereal; stir until evenly coated.
Press mixture evenly and firmly in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and cool.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together in top section of double boiler over hot, not boiling, water or in heavy small saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; spread evenly over cereal mixture.
Let stand in cool place until firm. Cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Makes 48.

title: fried rice(canton style)
directions: Cook the rice according to directions.
Heat the oil in a wok or pan.
Add garlic, vegetables and a little salt.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes, until the vegetables are cooked.
Take them out of the pan and set aside.
Add a little more oil to the wok.
Then add the sausage and shrimp.
Cook for 40 seconds.
Add to plate of vegetables.
Add more oil to pan, then ginger, white part of the onions and cooked rice.
Fry them for awhile.
Add the vegetables, sausage, shrimp and onion back to the wok.
Fry them for awhile. Add soy sauce and sugar.
Fry again until they look drier.
At last, put the eggs into the fried rice.
Fry until the eggs are cooked.
At this moment, the fried rice smells very good.
Serves 4 people.

title: pineapple no-bake cream pie
directions: Mix on low speed of mixer for 1 minute.
Pour into a baked pie shell (plain or graham cracker).
Top with Cool Whip.

title: creamed taco
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add other ingredients.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Serve over Doritos.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add others unbeaten.
Beat hard. Bake in loaf or layer pan 20 to 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: goop(kid's recipe)
directions: Will also need cookie sheets or trays or large tub, bowls, spoons.

title: sweet n sour bean salad
directions: Place vegetables in a large bowl.
Combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper in a saucepan and bring to boil.
(I use Sweet 'N Low, so I don't boil the dressing.)
Set aside to cool. Pour cooled dressing over vegetables; stir lightly and place in refrigerator several hours or overnight, tossing occasionally.

title: shirley's coconut cake
directions: Mix pineapple and 1 package frozen coconut in batter.
Mix together cream of coconut and milk.
Bake cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
After cake is baked, poke holes in cake with the end of a wooden spoon, while still hot, and pour the mixture of cream of coconut and condensed milk over cake.
Cool in refrigerator. Spread Cool Whip over top and cover with 1 package frozen coconut.

title: a-maizeing cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, mix corn, brown sugar and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add oil and beat until well mixed.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to liquids all at one time and stir until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes (until tests done).
(Cake may also be baked in 2 layer pans.)
Frost with caramel or cream cheese frosting.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute sausage.
Tear bread into pieces and spray Pam in bottom of pan.
Put bread pieces in pan.
Cover bread with sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs with rest of ingredients and pour over bread layer.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Put in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: gladys starr's coconut pie
directions: Combine 5 tablespoons sugar, flour and salt in double boiler. Add milk and egg yolks; stir until smooth.
Add 1 cup of the coconut.
Cook over boiling water 5 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cover.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to a full boil, stirring occasionally.
Continue to boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: m&m party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and brown and granulated sugars in a large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together; add to sugar-egg mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in 1/2 cup of M&M's.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Decorate tops with the remaining candies.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chili surprise
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan; cook meat, onion and garlic. Drain. Stir in remaining ingredients. Bring to the boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer partly covered for 35 minutes to an hour. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix both packages jello in 1 1/2 cups hot water.
Set aside. Mix all other ingredients.
Add to jello mix.
Chill 4 to 6 hours and serve.

title: saucy pepper steak
directions: Mix 1/3 can cream of mushroom soup, burger, crumbs, onion, peppers, egg and mushrooms.
Shape 6 to 8 solid patties.
Heat in hot oil.
Turn until brown.
Heat remainder of soup and spoon onto plate placing steak patties on top.
Great entree.

title: lisa's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan; cover with 2 strips bacon.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: Buy a large bag of taco chips and dip.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add corn, soups, sour cream, pimiento and seasonings.
Mix well.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Brown butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces; this should take about 2 months.
Add enough gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire about 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve 3,800.
If more diners are expected, then add 2 rabbits, but only if necessary because most people don't like "hare" in their stew.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown (50 to 60 minutes).

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli.
Place in bottom of casserole.
Steam chicken breasts until white.
Place on top of broccoli.
Mix the soup, mayo, sour cream and lemon juice and pour over.
Toss stuffing mix in melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: robbie's divinity(before starting, pray for it)
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup, water and salt on medium-high.
Stir until it starts to boil.
After it starts boiling, don't stir. Beat egg whites to a stiff peak.
To test boiling mixture (hard ball stage), dip spoon into it.
When the last drops off, it will string down like flying hair.
(No joke.)
Mix and slowly add to egg whites; mix on high.
Add vanilla.
Mix (high) for 5 minutes or until it gets hard.
Add nuts.
Spoon on wax paper.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well with hands.
Form into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (until brown).

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger; add onions and cook a few minutes.
Add 1/2 cup flour to soak up fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except macaroni and simmer 1/2 hour.
Cook macaroni separately and add just before serving.
Small amount of red wine may also be added for flavor.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine the vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimientos and 1/2 can of onion rings.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Pour over either meatballs or chicken. Serve heated.
Sauce may be doubled or tripled depending on serving size.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and slice.
Layer potatoes, thin sliced onion, salt and pepper, half of soup and half of cheese in baking dish.
Repeat the layers.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup chips and flour.
Beat cream cheese and then milk, eggs and vanilla.
Then add chips and flour.
Add 1/2 cup chips on top and bake 1 hour or until center is set at 350°.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Remove any fat from chicken.
Combine with remaining ingredients; simmer over low heat until well blended.
Place chicken pieces on a piece of foil and pour sauce over chicken. Fold foil and seal well.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook for an hour longer.
Serves 4.

title: grandma's easy peanut butter cookies
directions: The ingredients are correct. This recipe requires no flour.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add 3/4 cup flour and soda, a little at a time.
Combine milk and orange juice and add to flour mixture. Add nuts and fruits which have been coated with the remaining 3/4 cup flour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain. Add chopped bell pepper, onion, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and parsley. Season with salt, red and black pepper and garlic powder. Stir well.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
Boil noodles and add noodles and cream of mushroom soup to mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with shredded Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: braised beef ribs(microwave)
directions: Season ribs.
Preheat browning dish 4 minutes on high and brown ribs, meaty side down.
Wipe browning dish and preheat again to complete browning of all the meat.
Place meat back in dish, meaty side up on a microsafe rack.
Cover with lid or wax paper. Microwave on Medium for 25 minutes.
Turn dish halfway through cooking time.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli-rice whiz
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Saute onion and celery in butter. Stir rice and well drained broccoli; then add soup and Cheez Whiz. Season with pepper.
Spoon into greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.

title: coconut bars
directions: Beat first three ingredients well.
Press firmly into greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Crush Doritos in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Brown ground beef and onion. Combine soups and Ro-Tel. Bring to a boil.
Add meat and onion.
Pour over Doritos. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake in oven until cheese melts.

title: micro bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart microwave bowl.
Cook 4 minutes on High.
Stir and cook 4 minutes longer.
Cool at room temperature and then refrigerate.
Will keep in glass jar for weeks.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, mix onion, chunk chicken, chicken broth, shredded cheese and rice.
Cover; bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine first three ingredients; add remaining ingredients. Strain and serve hot.
Yield:
5 quarts.

title: cream cheese chocolate cupcakes
directions: Blend cheese, egg and sugar; beat well.
Stir in chocolate bits.

title: southern buttermilk brownies(serves 40)
directions: Bring margarine, water, oil and cocoa to a boil, then pour over sugar, flour and salt.
Next, add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and
pour into a greased and floured 11 x 16-inch pan; bake for 25 minutes in a 375° oven.
Ice immediately from oven.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Cut apples with a potato slicer.
Fill pie pan.
Mix cinnamon and sugar; sprinkle over apples.
Melt oleo; add sugar, flour and egg; pour and spread over apples. Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8
servings.

title: funshine fizz
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in container of an electric blender.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in club soda.
Serve immediately.
Yields 7 cups.

title: low calorie, low-fat blueberry apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottom and sides of an 8-inch square pan with waxed paper or use Teflon pan.
Mix blueberries, apples, lemon juice, raisins and 1/4 cup of apple juice in a bowl. Spread the blueberry/apple mixture in bottom of pan.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne and drain.
Cook beef and drain off grease.
Add to beef the onion, garlic, oil, tomato paste, water, oregano, basil and pepper.
While heating, combine last 7 items together into a cheese mixture in a large bowl.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture. Add vanilla, lemon juice and bananas.
Add dry ingredients with sour cream.
Pour in 3 coffee cans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: teriyaki glaze
directions: Mix all ingredients in a screw-top, quart size jar; store in refrigerator.
Glaze meat of your choice and cook as usual.

title: dijon chicken elite
directions: Wash and dry chicken parts.
Place crumbs in large bowl.
Add cheese and parsley and combine well.
Melt butter.
Add garlic after melting and simmer a few minutes to absorb flavor.
Remove from heat.
Add Worcestershire sauce, mustard and white pepper. Mix well.
When cool enough to handle, dip chicken pieces in butter mixture, then roll in bread crumb mixture.
Place in single layer on cookie sheet.
Pour any remaining butter mixture over chicken. Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Mix together peanut butter and butter in small bowl.
In larger bowl, mix together the remaining ingredients. Stir in peanut butter mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into balls and
freeze for half an hour.
Dip into melted chocolate and freeze until chocolate is hardened.
Insert a toothpick and enjoy.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients well, pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in 325° oven for one hour.

title: spinach-vegetable-shrimp salad
directions: Cook broccoli or peas and shrimp (do not overcook).
Chill. Wash spinach and mushrooms.
