Rub garlic or garlic powder on bowl. Slice tomato; cut cheese into small chunks.
Toss all vegetables and shrimp together; put cheese and olives on top.
Use dressing and seasonings of choice.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and clean mushrooms and pat dry.
Save stems for later use.
Thoroughly wash spinach; drain and finely chop.
Melt butter in skillet and cook mushrooms, cap-side down, until lightly browned.
Remove mushrooms and drain any liquid from inside caps. Set aside. Cook onions and mushroom stems in same skillet until tender and water evaporates.
Mix in garlic powder and Parmesan. Add spinach and salt and pepper and cook for 5 minutes, until spinach is completely wilted.
Add breadcrumbs and parsley. Combine well.
Let cool for a few minutes then stir in the Mozzarella.
Stuff filling into mushrooms and bake in hot 400°F. oven for 8-10 minutes, or until tops just start turning golden.

title: fiesta chuck roast
directions: You will also need 1 regular-size Reynold's oven bag.

title: crab on a muffin
directions: Slowly melt butter; mix in cheese, mayonnaise and seasoning. Fold in crabmeat.
Spoon on muffin.
Freeze.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with cherry pie filling before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pressure cooker chicken
directions: Heat oil in pressure cooker over medium high heat.
Sear chicken pieces a few at a time to seal in juices.
Remove from cooker.
Pour off excess oil and return chicken to pot.
Stir slightly to blend cream soup and broth and add it to pot, together with onion, celery, mushrooms and sprinkle salt and paprika over it.
Cover and pressure cook it for 8 minutes after weight starts rocking gently.
Quick, cool it under cold water.
Remove lid when pressure button has dropped.
Remove chicken to separate dish. Blend 2 Tbsp. flour with 1/4 c. water, and slowly stir flour mixture into liquid still in pot over medium heat to make gravy. Serve gravy over chicken.

title: eggnog trifle
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix, 2 tablespoons of the rum and nutmeg.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Fold in 1/2 the whipped topping.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into bite size pieces.
Put into casserole dish with okra.
Dice onion and stir into vegetables with salt and pepper.
Lay bacon on top.
Cook 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Stir in peanuts. Make a well in center and set aside.
Mix egg and milk until well blended; gradually blend into peanut butter.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients all at one time and stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: hash brown potato bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1/2 of cheese.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining cheese.
Cover with foil for 1 hour.
Remove foil; bake 15 minutes longer at 325°.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Add the peanuts.
Drop on cookie sheet.

title: lemon anise biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, whisk eggs, sugar, oil, rind, anise seeds, vanilla, lemon extract, salt and baking powder. Fold in flour; stir until smooth.

title: sausage bread
directions: Slowly brown sausage and onion just until sausage is done. Break up sausage into small bits as it cooks. Drain off any excess grease and then let mixture cool. Roll out thawed bread dough on lightly floured board until about 1/4-inch thick.

title: easy chicken stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into thin strips diagonally.
Brown meat in butter or shortening.
Add water, soup mix and undrained mushrooms.
Simmer this until meat is tender.
Add sour cream, blended with flour. Cook and stir until gravy thickens.
Serve over noodles.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix white and brown sugars with cinnamon in a large bowl.
Melt margarine.
Quarter each biscuit and coat with sugar mixture. Place evenly in Bundt pan.
Spread remaining sugar mixture evenly over biscuits and then pour margarine evenly over the biscuits. Preheat oven to 400°.
Place on middle rack and bake 12 to 14 minutes.
Take out of oven and invert onto a large plate while hot.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces and place in large bowl.
Cut onions and place over lettuce.
Top onions with celery.
Next, add frozen peas.
Sprinkle bacon over peas.
Sprinkle cheese over bacon layer.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Carefully spread over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: coconut candy
directions: Mix all ingredients in double boiler for 3 minutes. Bring to a boil or to soft ball stage.
Add oatmeal, coconut and nuts; mix together. Work fast as it hardens fast. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat well sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese until smooth; cool.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1/4 cup water; let stand 10 minutes.
Mix with soup and cream cheese.
Add celery and onion.
Gently stir in mayonnaise and shrimp (drained).
Place in a 2 quart mold; chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and pat onto cookie sheet (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake according to package directions.
Cool. Meanwhile, blend cream cheese, mayonnaise, dill weed and salad dressing mix in small bowl.
Spread evenly over baked crust. Sprinkle with toppings, then cheese.
Cut into 32 squares.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crushed vanilla wafers and 1 stick butter. Press in bottom of baking dish. Mix cream cheese and 1 stick butter until creamy. Add 10xx sugar. Mix well and pour over crumb mixture. Drain pineapple and put on cream cheese mixture. Slice bananas on top of this and put Cool Whip on top of this layer Place some pecans and maraschino cherries on top of whipped cream. Drizzle some chocolate syrup over all.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Put all the ingredients in a blender or food processor to prepare dip.
This dip is perfect with veggies.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil the first five ingredients together until brittle when tried in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla; add to corn.

title: curried seafood en coquille
directions: Cut scallops, shrimp and lobster into bite-sized pieces.
Melt butter in a skillet and saute minced garlic.
Add seafood.
Blend in flour and milk; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add the sherry.
The sauce should be thick.
Add mushrooms.

title: honey bars
directions: Mix and spread into a large oblong pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: linguine with clams
directions: In a large skillet saute onion and garlic in olive oil. Add clams, lemon,
tomatoes
and
seasonings.
Simmer
for
25 minutes.
Add wine	and
cook
uncovered until slightly thickened. This may be
done ahead of time.
Cool linguine according to package
directions.
Serve
sauce	over linguine.	Add Parmesan cheese.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and cook for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put chicken in a greased casserole dish. Pour broth and soup over chicken. In separate dish, add can of vegetables and peas, melted oleo, flour, milk and mayonnaise. Mix well. Pour over chicken. Bake at 425° for 35 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple cream cheese jello salad
directions: Place 1 cup Milnot in double boiler; add marshmallows and heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve lemon jello in cold water; add to hot mixture.
Mix pineapple, cream cheese, salad dressing, milk and nuts.
Combine with mixture in double boiler; pour into 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Place in refrigerate until set.
For top layer, make one package raspberry jello.
Cool and pour over first layer.

title: grandma's dumplings
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together. Add baking powder and flour, beat until thick like cookie dough. Drop by spoonfuls into boiling water or soup. Will rise when done.

title: fried won-tons
directions: Combine all ingredients except wonton wraps, oil and water. Cook on med to low heat until vegetables are tender.
Refrigerate mix to cool.
Put 1 tsp. mix onto each individual wonton wrap. Dab corners of wrap with water.
Fold over and seal by pinching edges of wrap.
Heat oil to medium high.
Fry wontons until lightly brown on each side.

title: wiener sauce
directions: To the browned hamburg, add onion and celery.
Saute until almost tender.
Drain fat, if any.
Add remaining ingredients; heat until bubbling.
Put the sauce through a meat grinder or food processor to reduce to a fine-textured sauce.
Serve over hot dogs or wieners in rolls.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Pour batter into large greased skillet.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook onion and green peppers in oleo until tender.
Combine in bowl with chicken and green chiles, which have been rinsed, seeded and chopped.

title: crab soup
directions: In a covered pot, simmer crab meat in boiling water for 20 minutes, which has been seasoned with celery seed, salt and pepper.
Then add parsley, light cream, milk and butter.
Makes about 5 servings.

title: haystack cookies
directions: Mix well, drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
When cookies are done, put half a marshmallow on top of warm cookies.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all.
Beat at medium speed 3 minutes.
Do not overbeat. Bake at 350° in three round pans for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cream together and spread on cake.

title: ham in a hurry
directions: Cook rice; lightly pan fry slice of ham.
Place ham on oven-proof platter or pan; pile rice on top of ham; spread grated yellow cheese on top of rice; place in hot broiler 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Each slice serves 2 to 3.

title: sauteed chicken(serves two to three)
directions: Dredge cutlets in flour.
Heat oil over medium-high heat. Saute in oil until cooked on both sides; be careful not to overcook.
Remove from pan; keep warm.
Turn up heat, stirring drippings in pan to brown.
Add butter to melt, then wine.
Turn heat to low.
Return cutlets briefly to pan, turning once.

title: margie's italian salad
directions: Combine salad ingredients.
Just before serving, toss with desired amount of salad dressing.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion, drain grease.
Place in casserole dish with beans, noodles, salt, garlic and soup.
Mix well and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Put ingredients in bowl and beat with electric mixer. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° until done, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sissy's chicken cacciatore
directions: Boil noodles with bell pepper, onions and tomato sauce until noodles, pepper and onions are tender.
Add mushrooms, seasonings and chicken.
Simmer 10 to 20 minutes.

title: frank 'n burger relish
directions: In large saucepan, blend Russian dressing, cornstarch and mustard; add vegetables.
Bring to a boil, then simmer.
Stir frequently until mixture is slightly thickened, about 5 minutes. Spoon into covered container, securing lid tightly.
Chill.
Store in refrigerator for up to 1 week.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups relish. Serve, if desired, on hamburgers and frankfurters.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Beat eggs. Add milk, sugar and salt. Add flour. Beat until smooth. Add sliced apples.
Add 1/4 cup oil in frypan.
Make as you would pancakes. Add oil as needed.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add liquid.
Bake 12 minutes at 450°. Yield:
12 biscuits.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until of semi-smooth consistency. Pour into a greased cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 375° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Top should be golden brown and edges slightly darker.

title: hurry up soup
directions: Prepare soup with water as directed on package.
Heat to boiling.
Add your choice of vegetables.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until all ingredients are tender and flavors are combined.
Sprinkle with eggs and grated cheese.

title: rosalynn carter's special cheese ring
directions: Mix and mold with hands into desired shape.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
When ready to serve, fill center with strawberry preserves.

title: green bean and onion salad
directions: Cook green beans until done, but still firm.
Add onion, salt and pepper, Italian seasoning, oil and vinegar.
Toss.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add sauce and simmer.
Cook macaroni.
Layer sausage/sauce mixture and macaroni in oblong baking dish, beginning with macaroni.
Top with pepperoni, mushrooms and cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: low-fat turkey macaroni
directions: Add spices and lemon to turkey; cook and drain.
Add cooked macaroni.
Pour spaghetti sauce over the mixture and add onion and peppers.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: scalloped corn supreme
directions: Heat corn and milk; gradually stir in egg.
Add 1 cup cracker crumbs, onion, pimento, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch round baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk chicken coating(makes it just like fried.)
directions: Soak skinned chicken 2 hours or more in buttermilk.
Blend the remaining ingredients until fine.
Coat both sides of chicken and bake at 400° in Pam sprayed pan for 1 hour, uncovered.
Coats 12 breast halves.

title: meatball tidbits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
In oblong baking dish, arrange meatballs in single layer.
Heat in microwave 6 to 7 minutes, stirring once and draining liquid when necessary. Serve with favorite sauce.

title: homemade sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Cook until onion
is tender.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: spring garden medley
directions: In large skillet, stir-fry vegetables in margarine until crisp-tender.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese and milk; stir until cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients; toss lightly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs,
oil, sugar, vanilla and spices.
Add zucchini, flour,
soda
and
baking powder.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes one large loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 475° until light brown.

title: hamburger-rice hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger in butter; add salt, pepper and onion. Add raw rice, mushroom soup, chicken rice soup, water, diced celery and mushrooms. Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°. Yield: 8 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in flavoring.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread(heritage recipe)
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar, add eggs, beat well, and bananas, beat well, add dry ingredients.

title: creamy cheesecake pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have crust ready.
Beat cream cheese slightly.
Add eggs, sugar, vanilla and lemon peel; beat until light and fluffy.
Pour into crust.
Bake until firm, about 25 minutes.
Spread Cheesecake Topping carefully over pie; cool. Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and water. Sift flour, salt, soda into liquid. Add 3 cups chopped (finely diced) fresh apples, 1 cup nuts, 2 teaspoons vanilla. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a lightly greased 13 x 9 inch pan.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Cut up strawberries.
Combine in large Dutch oven.
Slowly bring to a boil, stirring occasionally until sugar dissolves. Boil 12 minutes.
Skim foams off top.
Makes 4 half pints.

title: danish cauliflower soup
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Boil in chicken broth until tender.
Remove from broth; mash with fork.
Save broth.
Melt butter or margarine.
Saute celery and onion.
Add flour; mix well.
Add reserved chicken broth, a little at a time, stirring to keep smooth.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Add the cauliflower and half and half; heat thoroughly.
Do not boil.
Freezes well. Serves 5 to 6.

title: quick fudge
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large skillet, mix together chocolate, sugar, milk, margarine, corn syrup and vanilla.
Heat over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a full rolling boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss. Pour into prepared pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes 36 squares.

title: egg brunch casserole
directions: Spread bread cubes in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese and meat.
Combine eggs, milk and salt.
Beat well. Pour evenly over mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients except bread crumbs.
Add seasonings. Blend oil and milk; lightly stir in dry ingredients.
Combine butter and crumbs.
Drop dumplings into crumb mixture.
Drop dumplings on top of casserole.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes. Heat remaining soup and sour cream.
Serve with casserole. Yields 8 servings.

title: beef gravy
directions: Boil 2 cups water.
Add both flavors of bouillon cubes; completely melt in the water.
Add the onions and allow to simmer for approximately 2 minutes.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Put sugar and flour in saucepan; mix until free of lumps. Add pineapple. Cook over medium heat until thickened and clear. Cool. Pour into pie crust; top with miniature marshmallows or use large marshmallows, cut into quarters. Bake at 350° until marshmallows are golden.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Chop and saute onion and set aside.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add flour and blend well.
Add broth and enchilada sauce.
Stir until thickened.
Add sauteed onion.
Cut up tortillas into 1-inch pieces. Put 1/4 cup sauce in bottom of greased 2-quart casserole.
Layer tortilla pieces, chicken, cheese and enough sauce to cover.
Continue layers until casserole is full.
End with sauce.
Sprinkle some cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add walnuts.
Beat egg, add cranberry sauce and butter.
Add dry ingredients and stir until just blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: no cook chocolate macaroons
directions: Heat first six ingredients to a boil in large saucepan.
Mix minute oatmeal, salt and coconut into ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper until set.
Store in refrigerator.

title: low calorie barbecue chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place quartered chicken into baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil. Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until tender.
Yield: 4 servings, 125 calories per serving.

title: vanilla pineapple cake
directions: Mix sugar and pineapple until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over hot cake.
Let cool.
Pour pudding on cake.
Let set until firm. Spread Cool Whip on top of cake.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut on top.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix flour and warm water with spoon until it forms a ball and leaves side of bowl.
Pinch off about 1 tablespoon and pat into circles as flat as you can.
Poke a hole in the center to make sure it cooks through.
Melt shortening for deep drying.
Deep fry until golden brown.
It will puff up while cooking.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: company chicken
directions: Tenderize chicken breasts.
Pound until flat.
Pan-fry quickly on each side, only until turns white.
Roll into slice of ham and secure with a toothpick.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Season with garlic, salt and pepper.
Spoon mushroom soup (undiluted) on top and spread.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 325°. Serve over rice.

title: spoon corn bread
directions: Mix the ingredients together and pour into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
This can also be called Spoon Corn Bread Pudding.

title: pineapple-banana carrot cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients thoroughly.
Mix in flour and cinnamon.
Gently stir in remaining ingredients and pour into oblong baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cool, frost with Banana Frosting.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press hamburger tightly in greased dish.
Sprinkle on dry onion soup, then spread mushroom soup over that.
Put frozen Tater Tots on top and cook in a 350° oven until brown.

title: sea-fare salad
directions: Cook macaroni shells; drain well.
Combine water, lemon juice and bay leaf in skillet; bring to boiling.
Place frozen block of fillets in skillet.
Cover.
Simmer about 10 minutes or until fish just flakes; drain.
Flake slightly with a fork.
Cool.
Combine macaroni, fish, mixed vegetables, celery and onion in a large bowl. Mix Italian style dressing with lemon juice and pepper; add to macaroni mixture.
Toss salad lightly.
Cover; refrigerate 3 hours or until well chilled.
At serving time, add mayonnaise to mixture; toss lightly.
Line a serving platter with salad greens; mound salad in center.
Garnish with sliced cucumber.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Warm milk, sugar, margarine and salt to 120°.
Add warm milk mixture
to flour and yeast; beat for 3 minutes, using a spoon. Stir
in
as
much	flour
as you can of the remaining flour. Knead
3 to 5 minutes.
Shape into a ball; grease bowl lightly and
turn dough once.
Cover and let rise 1 1/2 hours (double in size).
Divide
in half and roll each half in 12 x 8-inch shape.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese mixed with tomatoes and peppers over low heat. Serve in fondue pot to keep hot.
Great with Doritos.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Make a white sauce by melting butter and mixing in flour. Gradually add chicken broth, mixing often to prevent lumps.
After the sauce thickens, add the chicken, salt and basil.
Set aside.

title: vegetable medley
directions: If using fresh veggies, clean and cut, then boil the vegetables until desired tenderness. In a separate saucepan, mix and melt the soup, sour cream, butter and cheese. Combine the cooked veggies, melted mixture and 3/4 can of the French fried onions and mix. Pour this into a buttered 1-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with more shredded Cheddar and the rest of the can of French fried onions and bake for 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Put ingredients in mixer and mix good.
Put into 9 x 12 pan.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in margarine.
Pour beef broth over meat.
Add all ingredients to meat/broth mixture.
Cook until tender-crisp. Thicken broth with cornstarch.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: marvelous macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl. Stir in egg whites and almond extract. Stir in nuts; mix well. Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheet. Garnish with candied cherry halves, if desired. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Remove from baking sheet immediately. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: out of this world pie(anna chenttes kitchen)
directions: Combine cherries, pineapple, sugar and flour in small saucepan and cook until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Add jello, red food coloring and vanilla and let cool.
Add pecans and bananas. Pour in pie crusts and chill overnight.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: another look at broccoli
directions: Butter casserole dish (13 x 9-inch).
Mix sour cream, salad dressing and onion.
Place broccoli in dish.
Cover with prepared mixture, then chestnuts and cheese.
Cover with cracker crumbs and drizzle with a little melted butter.
Bake in 350° oven for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked chicken kiev country style
directions: Melt butter. Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt. Dip breasts in butter, then crumb mixture. Place in ungreased 10-inch nonstick pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.

title: rice krispie surprise balls
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add marshmallows and melt slowly until syrupy.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
While warm, shape into small balls and roll in coconut flakes or candies.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: You will need pint jars.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat in large frying pan; add kidney beans and salt. Simmer 10 minutes.
Toss remaining ingredients (crush chips). Pour meat mixture over salad.
Better if served warm.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, tomato soup, mustard and celery seed. Heat to dissolve.
Cool slightly.
Pour over vegetables and chill.

title: coleslaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, Karo, lemon juice and salt.
Toss with about a quart of cabbage and mixed vegetables.
This is a vague recipe but is very easy coleslaw and tasty.
Adding red cabbage make a unique coleslaw in terms of color.

title: angel gingerbread
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco until creamy, then add molasses and eggs. Mix soda with buttermilk, then add flour and spices.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Cool and serve.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix together flour, soda and sugar.
Add buttermilk, oil and egg.
Mix well.
Add water a little at a time, stirring until right consistency, slightly lumpy.
Spoon or ladle batter onto preheated, oiled griddle.
Cook on one side until brown and batter begins to bubble.
Turn and brown on other side.
Serves 4.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all
together.
Pack down in 2 loaf pans real hard. Line pans with waxed
paper.
Place
in	refrigerator
or 3 days. Slice and serve.

title: fudgies
directions: In a large pan, mix the first 4 ingredients and boil for 1 minute after bringing to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat, then immediately add oatmeal, vanilla and salt.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: pirogi and fillings
directions: Mix ingredients well for 10 minutes.
Roll out on floured board and cut into 2 1/2 x 5-inch pieces.
Fill center of each piece with one of the following fillings.
Pinch edges well.
Drop into pot of salted boiling water and cook until Pirogi rises to the top of pot.
Cook for 6 more minutes.
Drain, strain in cold water.
Butter them or serve plain.

title: sofrito
directions: Blend all ingredients in the blender or in food processor. (I recommend the food processor instead of the blender.)
Keep some in the refrigerator and the rest you can freeze.
This can be used or put in your beans, stews, soups, rice or anything you want to add a Spanish flavor to.

title: chicketti
directions: Boil chicken in pot add just enough water to cover.
When chicken is done take out and cut into small pieces.
Add noodles and bouillon cubes to 1/2 of broth.
When noodles soften add soup and chicken pieces to mixture, cook thoroughly.
If mixtures starts to get too dry add more broth.
The finished product should be like spaghetti.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients; put into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: finger foods
directions: Spread cream cheese over tortillas or ham lunch meat. Sprinkle with garlic salt and onions.
Roll and cut into bite size pieces.
Pierce with toothpick.
Use picante sauce as dip.

title: microwave shrimp in garlic butter
directions: Place margarine in custard cup. Microwave on High for 30 to 45 seconds until melted. Stir in garlic powder and parsley flakes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cut up in small pieces.
In uncovered casserole, combine broccoli and rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.

title: marinated artichokes
directions: Drain artichokes, reserving liquid; quarter artichokes.
Set aside.
Combine reserved liquid, lemon juice and next 4 ingredients; stir well.
Add artichokes.
Cover and chill 8 hours, stirring occasionally.
To serve, drain artichokes and place on bed of lettuce leaves, if desired.
Yields 40 appetizers or can use as a salad.

title: zucchini cakes
directions: Form patties and fry.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix everything in a bowl except nuts. Beat 3 or 4 minutes. Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in an ungreased tube pan.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per directions on the box.
Melt caramels, butter and milk over low heat until melted and smooth.
Heat oven to 350°.
Liberally grease a 9 x 12-inch cake pan, preferably glass.

Pour 1/2 cake batter into the pan and bake for 15 minutes. Pour caramel mixture over the top and bake for 10 minutes. Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips evenly over the top; add rest of batter and bake for 20 minutes or until pick comes out clean of cake batter (you will see some melted chocolate and caramel so watch the cake carefully).

title: cheese and bean dip
directions: Heat all thoroughly in microwave and serve with chips.

title: travis's dill pickles
directions: Pack pickles in jars. Add Alum, dill seed and if wanted garlic powder to each jar. Boil water, vinegar, and salt. Pour into jars over pickles. Boil lids in water and seal.

title: huguenot torte
directions: Beat whole eggs in electric mixer or with rotary beater until very frothy and lemon-colored.

Add other ingredients in order. Pour into two well buttered baking pans, about 8 x 12-inches. Bake in 325° oven for about 45 minutes or until crusty and brown. To serve, scoop up with pancake turner (keeping crusty part on top); pile on large plate and cover with whipped cream and a sprinkling of the chopped nuts, or make 16 individual servings.

title: corn, broccoli and red pepper casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease or spray 12 x 8-inch baking dish (2-quart).
Rinse vegetables with warm water.
Set aside.
In large saucepan, melt margarine.
Saute onion until tender.
Blend in flour, pepper and mustard.
Stir until smooth.
Gradually add milk and cooking wine; heat until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Remove pan from heat.
Gently stir in eggs, cheese and vegetables.
Pour into baking dish; sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small bite size pieces.
Place in large salad bowl.
Arrange celery, eggs, peas, pepper, onion and meat in layers.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread over top of lettuce mixture, spreading to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Better if it stands in fridge overnight.
When you serve, reach to bottom to get some of each layer.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble bread and add oatmeal, milk and tomato sauce; let set.
In a separate large mixing bowl, combine ground beef, eggs and onion.
Mix by hand.
Add mixture from other bowl, along with A.1. sauce and salt.
Mix well by hand.
Empty into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Take out of oven and coat with ketchup.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: 7-day sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 24 hours and
drain.
Repeat
each day for 4 days, using fresh water each time.	On
5th day cut cucumbers in 1/4 inch rings. Combine vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Bring liquid to boil and pour over
sliced
cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain syrup and bring to a	boil.
Pour
over
cucumbers.
Repeat on sixth day. On the last
day;
drain
off
syrup
and bring to boiling point. Pack into hot
jars
and seal.
These are very crisp and delicious pickles.

title: squash casserole
directions: Prepare squash.
Steam sliced squash for 10 minutes on medium heat; drain.
Mix squash, diced onion, sugar, salt and eggs.
Add crushed cracker crumbs and margarine; stir well.

title: chili
directions: Season hamburger and
saute
in
1 tablespoon butter or margarine.	Set aside.
In	large
Dutch oven or kettle, brown bacon.
Add onion, diced
green
pepper
and
celery
and cook until tender.
Drain the hamburger.
Add hamburger and rest of the ingredients to the Dutch
oven
and cook slowly at least 2 hours, but can be cooked longer.
Serves 8.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook the macaroni. Put mayonnaise in a large bowl. Cut celery, onion and bell pepper into thin slices. Add to mayonnaise. Add cooked macaroni. Mix with a spoon. Sprinkle cheese in and mix a little at a time, it may clump together. Serves 10 to 15 people.

title: mark twain biscuits
directions: Measure flour after sifting.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix dry ingredients with pastry blender.
Add yeast and stir well.
Add buttermilk.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Roll out biscuits.
Place on greased pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.

title: pineapple turnovers
directions: By hand, work dry ingredients as for pie crust.
Flour board well and roll out.
Cut rounds with water glass.
Use flour as necessary.
Add 1 teaspoon preserves.
Fold over.
Seal edges with water.
Bake in 350° oven 25 minutes.

title: almost heaven cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch sheet cake pan.
After baking, prick cake with fork while cake is still warm.
Pour undrained pineapple over hot cake.
Blend pudding with milk and beat in cream cheese, a small amount at a time.
Spread over pineapple.
Cover with whipped topping.
Garnish with chopped nuts or coconut or both.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
The longer the cake is refrigerated the better the flavor.

title: hot corn casserole
directions: Place corn and jalapeno peppers in casserole dish.
In saucepan, melt cream cheese with milk and margarine.
Pour cheese mixture over corn and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ripe olive tuscan pot roast(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Brown beef on all sides in oil.
Add wine and water to meat. Cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours, until meat is fork-tender. Meanwhile, mix together remaining ingredients, except the butter. Set aside.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Mix well and pat in a
pan, bake at 350 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: low calorie chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and take off skin.
Layer a greased casserole dish with sliced onions.
Combine soup, drained peas, drained corn, pinched-up chicken and pinched-up bread and mix well.
Put on top of onions and bake at 350° until done.
Very good.
Low in calories and fat.

title: chicken-cheese enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken until tender (any method).
Cool and tear into bite-size pieces.
Combine next 3 ingredients in bowl.
In each flour tortilla, place 3 tablespoons tomato mixture, about 1/4 cup chicken, 3 tablespoons Ricotta cheese, sprinkle of Monterey Jack cheese and sprinkle of Cheddar cheese.
Fold tortilla over and place seam down in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour remaining tomato mixture over all the enchiladas and sprinkle more of both cheeses on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until bubbly.

title: mimi's chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and dry thoroughly.
Mix all ingredients and dip chicken in batter.
Heat oil (3 to 4-inches) to 375° in pan.
Fry until golden brown.

title: spinach spread
directions: Mix mayo, vegetable soup mix and sour cream.
Refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place spinach in bowl.
Chop water chestnuts finely.
Add to spinach in bowl.
Add sour cream mixture and shredded cheese to spinach.
Mix well.
Spread on bread slices and bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: taco platter dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese and French onion dip until spreadable. Spread on large round dish.
Pour the taco sauce over cream cheese mixture.
Add lettuce, tomatoes and Mozzarella cheese.
Dip up with tortilla chips or corn chips.
(Great for parties or any large gatherings.)

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; pound into meat.
Brown in hot oil.
Add tomato sauce and onion.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender.

title: easy bread pudding
directions: Combine milk and hot water.
Mix eggs and vanilla; add to milk mixture and pour over bread.
(I used leftover biscuits.)
Lightly butter or spray with nonstick spray a 1 1/2 or 2-quart baking dish.
Pour mixture into dish and place dish in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Combine other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: easy breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 pan. Cube bread. Brown and drain sausage or ham and spoon over bread.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over bread and meat.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread, meat and cheese and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over broccoli, bacon and onion mixture.
Add the almonds or other nuts.

title: popcorn candied
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pecans and almonds on cookie tray in single layer and bake 10 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently (nuts should be lightly brown).
Mix with popped corn. Melt sugar, butter and salt in small saucepan.
Mix with popped corn.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Cool in pan and store in tightly covered container.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook cored peppers in boiling water 5 minutes; drain.
Combine rice, beef broth, water and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and cook 15 minutes. Cook onion, small piece of green pepper and celery in butter until tender, not browned.
Stir in ham. Add to rice mixture (well).
Spoon into peppers.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over tops of peppers.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; cream margarine, eggs, vanilla and almond extract and mix with dry ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Drain and stir in butter.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Place in bottom of pie plate. Sprinkle 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese.
Brown meat and drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Pour mixture over cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for 15 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all brownie ingredients well.
Bake in greased pan for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: picante salsa
directions: Cut up tomatoes. Dice onions and peppers.
Using a large pot, bring to a boil and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add 3/4 cup cider vinegar, pickling salt and minced garlic. Stir well.
Pour into jars.
Yields 6 to 7 pints.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Shape beef into a patty. Place in the center of a large piece of heavy-duty foil. Add potato, carrot and onion. Sprinkle with seasoning blend and pepper. Fold foil and seal well. Place on baking sheet. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: kugel
directions: Combine all ingredients except cooked noodles and cinnamon. Add mixture to the noodles and sprinkle with cinnamon that has been placed in a well-buttered 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes until brown.
Great with almost any summer picnic or barbecue supper.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Set aside.
Brown rice in skillet and place chops on top of rice.
Add 1 or more cups water.
Put 1 tablespoon chili sauce on each pork chop, also 2 slices onion. Sprinkle hot pepper sauce over all.
Simmer until meat is cooked. If too dry, add more water.

title: steamed chocolate pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour, sifted with baking powder and salt.
Add beaten egg, milk and melted butter.
Steam 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix by hand just until mixed.
Do not overmix.
Cover and let stand in warm place for 1 hour to double in size.
Remove from pan on lightly floured board.
Press together, kind of folding together.
Do not knead.
Shape into 1 long roll.
Cut in half, making 2 long rolls.
Then, with knife, cut 12 pieces out of each roll, making 24 dinner rolls.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Combine all and serve with tortilla chips.

title: crab delights fettucini
directions: Cook fettucini according to package directions; drain.
Heat butter and garlic in skillet on medium heat until garlic is lightly browned.
Add half and half, crab delights and pepper. Heat for about 3 minutes, or until mixture just begins to bubble. Add Parmesan cheese; stir for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Toss crab delight sauce with fettucini.
Serve immediately with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and
rinse
the potatoes;
slice crossways, 1-inch thick. Place in the 1/2 gallon of water.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 10
minutes.
Remove
the potatoes and place in a roasting pan.
Add the cinnamon, nutmeg, flavor, sugar, syrup, butter and salt.
Cover with
2 to 3 cups of water and cook in moderate oven at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating until light.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating until smooth.
Add chocolate bits and nuts.

title: beef and rice skillet supper
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef, green pepper and garlic over medium heat for 10 minutes or until beef is no longer pink. Pour off any grease and add chili powder and salt. Add rice and mix well. Continue cooking for 2 minutes or until rice is hot; stir occasionally. Stir in peas and salsa and heat
through. Serve with grated Cheddar cheese and tortilla chips.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard-cooked egg in half lengthwise; remove yolk.
Crush yolk and mix with vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Refill whites with egg yolk mixture and garnish with paprika.
Yield:
1 serving, 1 egg.
Carbohydrate 0 g, protein 6 g, fat 6 g.
Calories per serving 78.
One serving = 1 meat medium fat exchange.

title: wiggles
directions: Fry bacon; add onions, green peppers and celery.
Fry ground beef separately; drain and mix with bacon mixture.
Take half of meat mixture and lay in the bottom of a pan or dish.
Place half of the cooked and drained noodles over the meat mixture.
Combine tomatoes, peas, salt, pepper and red pepper.
Layer this on top of the noodles.
Repeat with meat mixture, noodles and tomato mixture. Layer strips of cheese and drained mushrooms on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be made up ahead of time and not cooked.
Cover and freeze.
Take from freezer.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: refreshing punch
directions: Pour desired amount of mint ginger ale into punch bowl.
Add scoops of sherbet.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: beans a la thyme
directions: Combine all but last ingredient.
Simmer 5 minutes, then add baked beans.
Bake for 45 minutes in 375° oven.
Best assembled day before serving.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix together with spoon or hands.
Perfect for making snakes, letters, numbers, etc.
Tastes delicious!
(Play and eat if you dare!)

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Roll graham crackers to fine crumbs.
Add sugar and melted butter or oleo.
Mix together well and empty into a deep 8-inch pie pan.
With the back of tablespoon mold this into pie pan.

title: puppy chow
directions: Mix chocolate mix, butter, and peanut butter in a saucepan. Stir over low heat until melted and thin.
Coat cereal with mixture.
Put in brown sack with powdered sugar and shake to coat. Store in airtight container.

title: bavarian mints
directions: Melt chips and butter in a double boiler.
Remove from heat and add milk and flavoring, stirring until combined and pour into wax papered pan and cool.
Lift out and cut in cubes.
